WEBVTT

02:41.245 --> 02:42.829
My reminiscence.

02:43.539 --> 02:46.541
I always thought that
for such a lovely river,

02:46.625 --> 02:49.585
the name was mystifying,
Cape Fear.

02:50.254 --> 02:54.006
When the only thing
to fear on those
enchanted summer nights

02:54.341 --> 02:56.008
was that the magic
would end

02:56.093 --> 02:58.427
and real life would
come crashing in.

03:35.424 --> 03:38.467
GUARD: Okay, Cady,
the moment you've
been waiting for.

04:02.701 --> 04:05.036
Any people
coming for you, Cady?

04:05.495 --> 04:07.038
What about
your books?

04:07.122 --> 04:08.331
Already read them.

04:08.707 --> 04:10.333
(THUNDER RUMBLING)

04:27.684 --> 04:29.185
(THANKING IN SPANISH)

04:33.649 --> 04:35.024
(GREETING IN SPANISH)

04:36.068 --> 04:37.693
Hi. How are you?

04:37.861 --> 04:39.779
(SPEAKING SPANISH)

04:40.948 --> 04:42.198
(LAUGHING)

04:42.282 --> 04:43.616
This ropa limpia?

04:43.700 --> 04:46.786
No, no,
that means "clean."
These are dirty.

04:47.788 --> 04:50.122
LEIGH: The idea is to
resolve the tension.

04:50.207 --> 04:53.668
I need to find a motif
that's about movement.

04:54.878 --> 04:58.130
Not the most
mind-blowing concept
for a travel agency,

04:58.215 --> 05:00.049
but what the hey?

05:01.718 --> 05:03.094
Like an arrow,
maybe?

05:03.178 --> 05:04.512
Yeah, like an arrow.

05:05.055 --> 05:06.222
Maybe.

05:06.556 --> 05:10.017
But, see, then
the other aspect
is stability,

05:10.102 --> 05:11.936
a company
that you can trust.

05:13.146 --> 05:15.481
So if you can
balance those ideas

05:15.565 --> 05:19.110
in a way that's
pleasing to the eye,
then you got a logo.

05:19.194 --> 05:22.279
DANIELLE: Okay,
movement, stability,

05:22.364 --> 05:23.823
and an arrow.

05:24.741 --> 05:25.825
(LAUGHS)

05:25.909 --> 05:28.828
Okay, I'll think of
something for that one.

05:29.913 --> 05:31.122
(TAPPING LAP)

05:31.206 --> 05:32.707
Benjamin! Yes.

05:33.166 --> 05:36.293
They switched babies
on me at the hospital,
didn't they, huh?

05:36.378 --> 05:37.753
So, how'd you do
in there?

05:37.838 --> 05:39.463
Well,
I got the judge
to postpone

05:39.548 --> 05:41.841
the alimony hearing
for another 21 days.

05:41.925 --> 05:43.092
Great.

05:43.760 --> 05:47.179
Well, I've got till Monday
to find out which S and L
and which municipality

05:47.264 --> 05:48.848
my son-in-law
stashed all that money.

05:48.932 --> 05:50.182
Right. Right.

05:50.267 --> 05:51.892
But, anyway,
I thank you and
my daughter thanks you.

05:51.977 --> 05:53.185
Oh, you're welcome, Tom.

05:54.271 --> 05:57.148
Here's Daddy!

06:00.068 --> 06:01.694
Good-bye, Junior!

06:02.362 --> 06:03.779
(BIDDING FAREWELL
IN SPANISH)

06:06.783 --> 06:08.451
(BIDDING FAREWELL
IN JAPANESE)

06:08.535 --> 06:09.952
(CAT SCREECHING)

06:11.288 --> 06:13.706
Yes, that's very
creative, Junior.

06:18.962 --> 06:20.379
He liked me.

06:21.798 --> 06:24.717
All this time,
he actually liked me.

06:26.303 --> 06:27.970
(TIRES SCREECHING)

06:33.477 --> 06:35.019
WOMAN: You can't go in.
Your father's making

06:35.145 --> 06:38.272
a television appearance
for his campaign.
(MAX LAUGHING HYSTERICALLY)

06:38.356 --> 06:40.858
BEN: Dad!
Dad, I've got to
talk to you.

06:40.942 --> 06:43.069
BIG BEN: Oh, what the hell
are you doing here?
(LAUGHING CONTINUES)

06:43.153 --> 06:44.987
I'm about to go
on the air.
(COUGHS)

06:45.238 --> 06:46.989
What is this smoke?

06:50.077 --> 06:52.411
Excuse me.
Excuse me.

06:52.621 --> 06:54.288
(CONTINUES LAUGHING)

06:57.501 --> 06:59.752
Come on,
let's move our seats.

06:59.836 --> 07:01.253
(MOVIE CONTINUES)

07:10.972 --> 07:13.182
BEN: Okay,
then I quit
as your son.

07:15.352 --> 07:18.104
So, do you believe
that annoying loser guy?

07:18.188 --> 07:20.106
Dad, you should have
just punched him out.

07:20.190 --> 07:21.273
What?
Just punched him out?

07:21.358 --> 07:22.358
Yeah.

07:22.442 --> 07:23.609
What do you mean?
You boxed.

07:23.693 --> 07:25.402
You could've
shoved him around,

07:25.487 --> 07:26.737
shut him up.
Yeah. Yeah.

07:26.822 --> 07:28.030
I could take you.
Careful.

07:28.115 --> 07:29.573
That's who
I could take.

07:29.658 --> 07:31.283
You could've even
kicked him in the face.

07:31.368 --> 07:32.535
Kicked him
in the face?

07:32.619 --> 07:35.037
You know how to fight dirty.
You do that for a living.

07:35.747 --> 07:38.207
(LAUGHING)
Oh, real cute, Leigh.
(GRUNTS)

07:38.875 --> 07:40.876
Let's sit outside.
How much
do I owe you?

07:40.961 --> 07:42.169
It's taken care of.

07:42.254 --> 07:43.712
Taken care of? Who?

07:43.922 --> 07:45.089
There.

07:58.478 --> 08:01.522
Girls, girls, come on,
let's sit inside.

08:01.606 --> 08:02.773
Yeah, let's sit inside.

08:20.083 --> 08:21.417
(GRUNTING)

08:26.756 --> 08:27.882
(GRUNTS)

08:27.966 --> 08:29.925
Whoa, Mr. Perfect Form.

08:30.510 --> 08:32.385
No, no, I don't.
You've got to...
What?

08:32.470 --> 08:33.511
Look.
What?

08:33.597 --> 08:35.764
You got to
snap your wrist
on the backhand.

08:35.849 --> 08:38.683
Usually I like
a little music
at this point, Sam.

08:38.768 --> 08:40.727
MAN: Sam, I want to play
in this lifetime.

08:40.812 --> 08:43.105
All right,
all right,
all right.

08:43.523 --> 08:44.607
You got to
snap your wrist.

08:44.691 --> 08:45.774
Tag.

08:46.443 --> 08:49.653
You know, we should
stop doing this
for a while.

08:49.738 --> 08:53.032
Doing... Doing what?
We're not doing anything.

08:53.116 --> 08:54.867
Yeah, I know that.
Yet.

08:54.951 --> 08:57.745
Okay. No, fine, fine.
Maybe you're right.

08:58.121 --> 08:59.455
Why?
Does your wife mind?

09:00.081 --> 09:01.874
Well, my wife doesn't
even know you exist,

09:01.958 --> 09:03.959
which, most certainly,
is for the best, you know.

09:04.044 --> 09:05.419
Why's that?

09:06.546 --> 09:09.131
God, you know, Lori,
you know why you have
to ask that question?

09:09.257 --> 09:10.883
'Cause you've
never been married.
Why?

09:10.967 --> 09:12.301
Is marriage synonymous
with deception?

09:12.385 --> 09:13.719
(LAUGHING)
No, no, no.

09:13.803 --> 09:16.180
It's just that,
you know,
when two people...

09:16.264 --> 09:18.849
When two people
get married

09:18.934 --> 09:21.477
and they live together
for a long time,
you know...

09:23.688 --> 09:26.815
I like hanging out
with you, you know,
so sue me.

09:26.900 --> 09:28.400
(BOTH LAUGHING)

09:28.485 --> 09:31.070
You're funny,
and you're cute,
and, I don't know...

09:31.154 --> 09:34.531
We talk about the courts
and which judge is senile

09:34.616 --> 09:37.201
and which one wears a gun
under his robe and...

09:37.285 --> 09:38.994
Oh, God.
You know, Lori,

09:39.079 --> 09:42.373
another time, another place,
and who knows, you know?

09:44.209 --> 09:45.251
Tomorrow?

09:45.335 --> 09:46.335
Yeah,
it's a light docket.

09:46.670 --> 09:48.128
No, no, no, no,
I won two out of three.

09:48.213 --> 09:49.672
Let's make it
the best out of five.

09:51.675 --> 09:52.883
All right, well,
that's good, actually,

09:52.968 --> 09:54.969
because today
I let you win.

09:55.178 --> 09:56.595
(LAUGHS) Sure you did.

09:56.680 --> 09:57.930
See you.
Sure you did.

10:03.853 --> 10:04.937
Hey.

10:05.689 --> 10:06.939
Free as a bird,
apparently.

10:07.023 --> 10:08.774
You go everywhere
you want with whomever.

10:08.858 --> 10:10.401
That much freedom
could maybe get
a fellow into trouble.

10:10.485 --> 10:11.485
What do you think?

10:11.569 --> 10:12.861
I'd like my keys.

10:12.946 --> 10:15.030
Could it be
you don't remember me?

10:15.365 --> 10:16.699
Oh, yeah, sure,
I remember you.

10:16.783 --> 10:18.033
You were
at the movie house
the other night.

10:18.118 --> 10:20.244
Oh, I'm disappointed.
I'm hurt.

10:20.328 --> 10:22.121
I would like my keys.

10:23.873 --> 10:25.165
Max Cady.

10:26.668 --> 10:28.043
You look the same.

10:28.295 --> 10:30.254
Maybe 15 pounds heavier.

10:30.338 --> 10:31.588
But they say
the average man

10:31.673 --> 10:34.091
gains a pound a year
till he's about...

10:34.175 --> 10:35.968
(CHUCKLING) Come on.

10:37.721 --> 10:39.888
Gains a pound a year
till he's about 60.

10:39.973 --> 10:43.058
Me? I dropped a pound
every year
of my sentence.

10:45.437 --> 10:47.855
Atlanta, '77.
You got it. July.

10:48.815 --> 10:51.191
Fourteen years since
I held a set of keys.

10:54.612 --> 10:56.780
Well, you look good,
healthy.

10:57.073 --> 11:00.659
Thank you. 'Cause it's
a struggle to stay healthy
in the joint.

11:00.744 --> 11:02.786
But you wouldn't
know about that,
would you?

11:03.079 --> 11:04.788
If you were me,
they would stick you
with the white trash.

11:04.873 --> 11:06.373
They don't strike
a lick of work all day.

11:07.500 --> 11:11.378
In fact,
this little old cigar
is my only vice

11:11.463 --> 11:15.007
'cause I needed
a vice in the joint
to remind me I was human.

11:16.468 --> 11:18.844
So, what brings you
to New Essex?

11:18.928 --> 11:20.554
Oh, the climate.

11:22.140 --> 11:23.474
Boy, the South.

11:23.558 --> 11:27.102
I'm thinking of
settling right down here
in New Essex, Counselor.

11:28.605 --> 11:29.688
Have you
been following me?

11:29.773 --> 11:31.065
It's a small town.
Everywhere you turn,

11:31.191 --> 11:32.733
I guess, we're gonna
run into each other.
(STARTS ENGINE)

11:32.817 --> 11:34.109
Well, take care,
Mr. Cady.

11:34.194 --> 11:35.361
You, too.

11:39.115 --> 11:40.491
You're gonna learn
about loss.

11:40.575 --> 11:41.992
What?

11:52.128 --> 11:53.962
Dad, could you...

11:54.172 --> 11:55.506
Hmm?

11:55.799 --> 11:57.383
Oh, I'm sorry, Dani.

11:58.426 --> 12:00.344
What're you working on?
It's English.

12:00.970 --> 12:03.055
We're supposed to read
Look Homeward, Angel,

12:03.139 --> 12:05.057
which is a kind
of reminiscence,

12:05.141 --> 12:07.893
and we have to
attempt something
in the same style.

12:09.979 --> 12:12.022
What's it about,
your reminiscence?

12:13.233 --> 12:14.733
The houseboat.

12:16.361 --> 12:18.320
Oh, the houseboat.

12:23.993 --> 12:25.327
LEIGH: It's not even
July 3rd yet.

12:25.412 --> 12:26.412
Yeah.

12:26.496 --> 12:27.788
Yeah. I was thinking
we ought to take

12:27.872 --> 12:29.123
two weeks off and
go up to Wilmington

12:29.207 --> 12:30.707
like the old times,
dock the houseboat.

12:30.792 --> 12:32.459
I wanted to
in early June.

12:32.544 --> 12:34.169
Remember you said
you didn't have time
this summer.

12:34.254 --> 12:35.295
I probably don't.

12:35.380 --> 12:36.797
Yeah, well,
now I don't, either.

12:36.881 --> 12:39.341
Besides,
Dani's got summer school
till Labor Day.

12:39.426 --> 12:40.843
Is it really
that critical

12:40.927 --> 12:43.303
that she can't
miss two damn weeks?

12:43.388 --> 12:45.931
(SIGHS) Well, you know,
the alternative was
to expel her.

12:46.516 --> 12:48.767
Besides,
maybe this Drama teacher
from the college

12:48.852 --> 12:50.727
will get her excited
about something,
you know?

12:50.812 --> 12:52.855
Yeah, about him,
probably.

12:53.273 --> 12:55.023
I mean, why'd they have
to make such a stink,

12:55.108 --> 12:57.276
like she was on heroin,
or something?

12:57.360 --> 12:59.528
I mean, marijuana,
what's marijuana?

12:59.612 --> 13:01.572
You and I smoked
a little dope
in our time.

13:01.656 --> 13:02.739
Yeah.

13:02.824 --> 13:04.074
You know,
in some cultures,

13:04.159 --> 13:05.784
it's considered
almost a sacrament.

13:05.869 --> 13:07.870
Of course,
I realize in ours,
it's forbidden.

13:07.954 --> 13:13.125
Right up there with incest
and necrophilia
and bestiality.

13:13.209 --> 13:14.626
Honey. Honey. Honey.

13:14.711 --> 13:16.753
Worship of idols,
cannibalism.

13:16.838 --> 13:17.921
Do that again.

13:18.548 --> 13:19.715
What?

13:19.799 --> 13:21.216
Do that again.

13:21.551 --> 13:22.843
(LAUGHS)

13:25.847 --> 13:27.598
(FIRECRACKERS EXPLODING)

15:12.787 --> 15:15.539
Sam. Sam,
somebody's out there!
What?

15:16.541 --> 15:18.834
No, leave the light off.
Leave it off.

15:22.297 --> 15:24.256
I saw him when
the fireworks went off.

15:24.340 --> 15:25.424
(MURMURING)

15:25.508 --> 15:26.633
What?

15:27.093 --> 15:28.885
I think I talked
to him this afternoon.
You know him?

15:30.680 --> 15:33.181
I want you the hell
off my property!

15:46.195 --> 15:47.529
He's gone.

15:53.328 --> 15:56.830
He said, "I'm gonna
make you think
about loss."

15:56.914 --> 16:00.334
Or, "I'm gonna make
you learn about loss."
Something like that.

16:00.585 --> 16:02.336
That's very poetic.

16:03.254 --> 16:04.630
So, who is he?
Where did he come from?

16:04.714 --> 16:05.881
Well, he's from...

16:06.758 --> 16:09.301
Come on, Leigh,
get the dog off.
Ben, get down.

16:09.552 --> 16:10.677
(LAUGHS)

16:10.762 --> 16:12.554
He doesn't
mind me at all.

16:12.639 --> 16:14.139
Leigh, he's your dog.
Come on.

16:14.766 --> 16:16.683
No, he shouldn't
be up on the table.

16:17.018 --> 16:19.186
You're gonna have
dog hairs in the tea
and everything.

16:19.270 --> 16:21.021
Get down.
So where's he from?

16:21.105 --> 16:23.899
Oh, he's from the hills,
Pentecostal crackers,
you know.

16:25.360 --> 16:27.069
What was he
in prison for?

16:28.905 --> 16:30.489
I think it was battery.

16:30.573 --> 16:32.032
You think
it was battery?
Yeah.

16:32.116 --> 16:33.492
I mean, well,
who did he batter?

16:33.576 --> 16:35.827
Did he batter a man?
Did he batter a woman?
What?

16:35.912 --> 16:36.995
I don't know.

16:37.080 --> 16:40.248
It was 14 years ago.
You know, it's kind of...

16:40.917 --> 16:42.918
I really don't remember.

16:44.003 --> 16:46.088
What does he want
with you?

16:46.881 --> 16:49.675
He's just trying
to bug us,
just messing around.

16:49.759 --> 16:52.094
You know,
he's an ex-con,
so he's just...

16:52.595 --> 16:56.598
You know,
he's probably upset
at the lawyer.

16:57.350 --> 16:58.684
Yeah, your clientele.

16:58.768 --> 16:59.893
Yeah.

17:03.773 --> 17:04.856
Bye, Dad.
Bye, Dani.

17:04.941 --> 17:05.982
You look tired.

17:06.067 --> 17:08.193
Thanks.
I needed that. Leigh.

17:08.944 --> 17:10.069
Leigh,
I don't want
to alarm her,

17:10.154 --> 17:12.196
but I'd rather Dani
didn't wander out alone

17:12.281 --> 17:14.156
on her soul-searching
walks in the woods

17:14.242 --> 17:15.701
at least till I've
started a few things,

17:15.785 --> 17:17.202
maybe even talked
to the boss.

17:17.286 --> 17:18.869
What if she takes
Benjamin with her?

17:18.954 --> 17:20.497
What? Big Ben,
our guard dog?

17:20.580 --> 17:22.457
What's he gonna do,
lick him to death?

17:22.541 --> 17:24.084
Just tell her.
LEIGH: Tell her what?

17:24.167 --> 17:25.919
I hardly know anything
about the man.

17:26.002 --> 17:27.503
I don't mean
his biography.

17:27.588 --> 17:28.922
Just there's
some creep around.

17:29.006 --> 17:31.508
And if you see him again,
call the cops
and then call me.

17:31.592 --> 17:33.844
What about a weapon,
you know?

17:33.928 --> 17:36.888
In case things get
exciting around here.

17:36.973 --> 17:38.974
Look, Leigh,
would you really
feel more secure

17:39.058 --> 17:40.434
with a loaded gun
in the house?

17:40.518 --> 17:42.853
We'd probably end up
using it on each other.

17:42.937 --> 17:44.396
Or Dani would.

17:44.480 --> 17:46.690
He's not gonna do anything.
He just got out of prison.

17:46.774 --> 17:49.067
He doesn't want
to go right back.
All right?

17:51.738 --> 17:53.321
Call Lee Heller.

17:53.906 --> 17:55.407
Lee is
a colorful character,

17:55.491 --> 17:57.409
but he's still the best
criminal lawyer
in the state.

17:57.827 --> 17:59.661
Good.
Bonnie,
get me Lee Heller.

18:00.329 --> 18:02.748
Sam, you defended
this guy, right?

18:02.832 --> 18:03.790
Right.

18:03.875 --> 18:05.751
So, what makes you think
he wants to harm you?

18:05.835 --> 18:07.794
Yesterday I was
getting in my car.

18:07.879 --> 18:10.630
The guy comes up,
we have a little
conversation.

18:10.715 --> 18:13.967
He says to me,
"You're gonna
learn about loss."

18:15.261 --> 18:18.180
That'd hardly qualify
under the terrorist
threat statutes.

18:18.514 --> 18:21.308
Oh, come on, Tom,
for Christ's sake,
the guy's an ex-con.

18:21.392 --> 18:24.394
You know
as well as I do
what that means.

18:24.479 --> 18:27.189
I mean, last night,
there he was,
he was behind our house.

18:27.440 --> 18:28.940
Ah. Attempted B and E.

18:29.025 --> 18:30.275
No, not exactly.

18:30.359 --> 18:33.987
I mean,
he was sitting on a wall
that bounds our property.

18:34.071 --> 18:36.782
(LAUGHS) That's not
even trespassing, Sam.

18:36.866 --> 18:38.492
I mean, come on.
What can I say?

18:38.576 --> 18:40.160
I mean,
get a restraining order.

18:40.244 --> 18:43.580
I did.
I filed one this morning.
The hearing's in 10 days.

18:43.664 --> 18:47.042
Good. Good.
I mean, you know,
anything I can do.

18:47.126 --> 18:49.211
Tom, 14 years ago

18:50.713 --> 18:54.049
in this case
I had a report
on the victim.

18:54.383 --> 18:56.218
It was a rape case.
That's right.

18:56.302 --> 18:58.637
Rape and
aggravated sexual battery.

18:58.721 --> 19:00.472
Anyway,
I had a report
on this victim

19:00.556 --> 19:03.558
and it came back that
she was promiscuous.

19:05.603 --> 19:06.686
And...

19:07.897 --> 19:09.314
I buried it.

19:10.733 --> 19:11.983
Whew.

19:14.028 --> 19:15.070
Anybody else know
about this?

19:15.196 --> 19:16.321
No, no, no,
I buried it.

19:16.405 --> 19:17.531
I mean,
I didn't show it
to the client,

19:17.615 --> 19:19.825
I didn't show it
to the prosecution.

19:19.909 --> 19:22.786
But if you had seen
what this guy had
done to this girl...

19:23.162 --> 19:26.039
"In every
criminal prosecution,
the accused shall have

19:26.123 --> 19:27.999
"the Assistance of
Counsel for his defense."

19:28.084 --> 19:29.251
I know
the Sixth Amendment.

19:29.335 --> 19:30.669
I believe in
the Sixth Amendment.

19:30.753 --> 19:33.296
I mean, that's why I left
the Public Defender's Office.

19:33.381 --> 19:36.174
There was no way
to serve the law
in that capacity.

19:36.259 --> 19:37.259
Some folks just
don't have the right

19:37.343 --> 19:38.426
to the best defense,
huh, Sam?

19:38.511 --> 19:40.679
No! Of course
they deserve
the best defense!

19:40.763 --> 19:43.473
But, I mean,
if you had seen what
he did to this girl...

19:43.558 --> 19:44.766
You buried the report.

19:44.851 --> 19:46.268
I mean, if it was
your own daughter, Tom.

19:46.853 --> 19:49.354
Yeah, I mean...
Buried the report.

19:49.814 --> 19:51.189
Jesus, Sam.

19:52.859 --> 19:54.234
Oh, God.

19:55.945 --> 19:57.320
(SIGHS)

19:58.781 --> 20:01.157
But I don't see how
he could know that.

20:01.242 --> 20:02.409
I mean,
he was illiterate.

20:03.202 --> 20:04.661
I mean, I had to
read everything to him,

20:04.745 --> 20:06.162
the probable
cause affidavit,

20:06.247 --> 20:08.540
the arrest reports,
everything.

20:10.293 --> 20:12.711
There's no way
he could know that.

20:23.931 --> 20:28.059
Hey, Dani,
it's so quiet out here,
and the light's so perfect,

20:28.144 --> 20:31.313
why don't you get your book
and come out here and read?

20:31.397 --> 20:32.480
Why?

20:33.566 --> 20:34.983
I told you why.

20:35.484 --> 20:39.321
Well, is it because
he's like a flasher
or just a peeper?

20:39.780 --> 20:42.198
What do you know
about that?
A flasher?

20:42.283 --> 20:45.035
Oh, you don't think
I've been flashed
before?

20:45.328 --> 20:47.412
Oh, well,
I certainly didn't mean
to insult you.

20:47.496 --> 20:49.247
I'm sure you've
been flashed before.

20:49.332 --> 20:52.125
Look, if you want to
come out, come on out.
If you don't, go on.

20:52.501 --> 20:54.252
Do whatever you want.

20:55.338 --> 20:57.172
Oh, but don't
go outside.

21:03.137 --> 21:04.930
CADY: Afternoon,
Counselor.

21:08.851 --> 21:10.894
What do you want,
Mr. Cady?

21:11.854 --> 21:13.188
(GIRLS LAUGHING)

21:19.153 --> 21:21.613
They're great at
that age, ain't they?

21:21.697 --> 21:24.157
All those discoveries
ahead of them.

21:24.241 --> 21:25.533
You're lucky,
Counselor.

21:26.118 --> 21:28.828
My own daughter,
she don't even know me.

21:29.246 --> 21:32.123
After I went inside,
her mama told her
I was dead,

21:32.208 --> 21:34.125
which, in a way,
I was.

21:34.627 --> 21:38.546
Look, Mr. Cady,
I realize that
you suffered.

21:38.714 --> 21:39.756
(LAUGHS)

21:39.840 --> 21:42.759
I mean,
I understand your problem,
but, I mean, why me?

21:43.552 --> 21:46.221
I was your lawyer.
I defended you.

21:46.931 --> 21:49.808
I mean,
why not badger the D.A.
Or the judge?

21:49.892 --> 21:50.976
(LAUGHING) "Badger."

21:51.060 --> 21:52.102
Yeah. Why not them?

21:52.770 --> 21:55.021
Yeah. Why not them?
"Badger."

21:56.107 --> 21:59.109
Best I remember,
they was just doing
right by their jobs.

21:59.193 --> 22:01.695
Oh, I didn't do my job?
Is that right?

22:02.446 --> 22:05.490
Look, I pleaded you out to
a lesser occluded offense.

22:05.574 --> 22:07.826
You could've gotten rape
instead of battery.

22:07.910 --> 22:10.161
Oh, I'd have been up
for parole either way
in seven years

22:10.246 --> 22:11.454
according to the
Georgia penal code.

22:11.539 --> 22:12.539
Rape is
a capital offense.

22:12.623 --> 22:15.166
I mean,
you could've gotten life,
you could've done death.

22:15.251 --> 22:18.128
You could be sitting
on death row right now.

22:19.922 --> 22:22.465
I learned to read
during my stretch.

22:23.092 --> 22:26.678
First,
Spot Goes to the Farm,

22:26.762 --> 22:30.056
then Runaway Bunny,
then law books, mostly.

22:32.101 --> 22:34.185
Did you know that
after I discharged you,

22:34.270 --> 22:36.104
I acted as
my own attorney?

22:36.689 --> 22:38.690
Applied several times
for an appeal.

22:38.774 --> 22:40.650
No, I didn't know that.

22:42.111 --> 22:43.361
Mmm-hmm.

22:43.446 --> 22:45.530
So, here we are,

22:45.614 --> 22:49.117
two lawyers,
for all practical purposes,
talking shop.

22:49.785 --> 22:52.037
All right. How much
do you want, Mr. Cady?

22:53.289 --> 22:54.873
How much
do I want what?

22:54.957 --> 22:57.083
How much money
do you want?

22:57.418 --> 23:01.004
Money? Counselor,
do I look destitute
to you?

23:01.088 --> 23:04.257
Well,
I'm open to discussion,
within reasonable limits.

23:07.094 --> 23:08.178
You ever been a woman?

23:08.596 --> 23:09.637
A what?

23:09.722 --> 23:10.764
A woman.

23:12.475 --> 23:15.727
Some fat, hairy,
ugly hillbilly's
wet dream?

23:20.066 --> 23:21.191
Look, I realize that
you suffered in prison.

23:21.275 --> 23:22.275
Suffered.

23:22.401 --> 23:23.693
There's no question
about that.
"Suffered."

23:23.778 --> 23:26.654
You don't know
what suffering is,
Counselor.

23:27.364 --> 23:29.574
Like it says
in Galatians 3,

23:29.658 --> 23:32.494
"Have ye suffered
so many things in vain?"

23:33.829 --> 23:34.871
Yeah.

23:34.955 --> 23:36.915
I learned from
the get-go in the joint
to get in touch

23:36.999 --> 23:40.668
with the soft
nurturing side of myself,
the feminine side.

23:45.674 --> 23:50.386
Well, I'm open to
some sort of discussion
on compensation.

23:51.597 --> 23:54.057
What shall be
my compensation, sir,

23:54.141 --> 23:57.352
for being held down
and sodomized
by four white guys

23:57.436 --> 23:59.395
or four black guys?

24:00.815 --> 24:02.899
Shall my compensation
be the same?

24:02.983 --> 24:06.027
What is the formula
for compensation, sir?

24:06.403 --> 24:08.696
How about $10,000
in cash?

24:11.700 --> 24:12.909
Do I...

24:16.997 --> 24:18.623
Well, let's just
break that down.
No.

24:18.749 --> 24:20.792
Now, wait, wait,
wait a minute.
Let's just break it down.

24:20.876 --> 24:22.252
You see,
that figure just came
to the top of my head.

24:22.336 --> 24:23.920
Well, let's just say,
for argument's sake,

24:24.004 --> 24:27.132
let's say $20,000,
let's say $30,000.

24:27.216 --> 24:29.342
Say...
I'll tell you what.
Let's say $50,000.

24:30.511 --> 24:32.804
$50,000 into 14 years.

24:32.888 --> 24:36.641
Fourteen years times
365 days is about...

24:37.184 --> 24:38.935
I say about 5,000 days.

24:39.019 --> 24:43.398
Now,
you divide that by $50,000,
and that's like $10 a day.

24:44.150 --> 24:46.609
(LAUGHING) That's
not even minimum wage.

24:46.694 --> 24:50.572
To say nothing about
the family that I lost,
the respect that I lost.

24:51.031 --> 24:52.991
I don't think you really,
really understand

24:53.075 --> 24:55.160
what we're
talking about here.

24:55.244 --> 24:56.744
Fourteen years.

24:57.121 --> 24:58.746
(WATCH BEEPING)

24:59.039 --> 25:00.748
Whoops. Uh-oh.

25:00.833 --> 25:01.916
Gotta git.

25:01.959 --> 25:03.793
(STARTS ENGINE)
I'm late for
another appointment.

25:09.091 --> 25:11.050
Sam, my man,
I got some good news.

25:11.135 --> 25:13.052
I got the bank,
I got the account number.

25:13.137 --> 25:14.971
Great. I'll call your
son-in-law's lawyer,

25:15.055 --> 25:16.139
tell him we're going
to court.

25:16.223 --> 25:18.516
Mr. Bowden,
your wife's
on line one.

25:18.601 --> 25:20.560
Ask her to hold.
I got to make
a quick call.

25:20.644 --> 25:22.729
I wouldn't make
that call, Sam.
The way I'd...

25:22.813 --> 25:24.898
Mr. Bowden,
she says it's urgent.

25:29.361 --> 25:30.403
Yeah?

25:32.990 --> 25:36.451
...these kind of horrible,
high-pitched howls.

25:36.535 --> 25:39.162
They sounded like
he was screaming,

25:39.246 --> 25:40.580
and then Dani
came running in,

25:40.664 --> 25:41.915
and I...

25:43.459 --> 25:45.126
I called the vet.

25:47.087 --> 25:49.380
Then it was so weird
because

25:52.843 --> 25:55.178
it was like
he was winding down,

25:56.096 --> 25:59.390
just winding down
like an old clock.

25:59.808 --> 26:02.727
And then,
all of a sudden,
he just stopped.

26:04.521 --> 26:06.356
He had this kind of...

26:08.359 --> 26:11.319
His eyes just wide open,
and this kind of

26:13.572 --> 26:15.114
surprised look.

26:16.951 --> 26:18.326
And then...

26:21.705 --> 26:23.331
And then he died.

26:25.334 --> 26:28.795
He just died,
before the vet
even got here.

26:31.048 --> 26:32.674
What did the vet say?

26:33.342 --> 26:34.467
That he was poisoned.

26:34.551 --> 26:35.677
Poisoned?

26:36.095 --> 26:37.637
What kind of a poison?

26:39.014 --> 26:40.515
I don't know
what kind of poison.

26:40.599 --> 26:41.599
Oh, Jesus!

26:41.684 --> 26:43.142
Leigh, I told you not
to let him out.

26:43.227 --> 26:44.477
I didn't let him out!

26:44.561 --> 26:45.603
Well, then how...

26:45.688 --> 26:47.605
I didn't let him out!
Stop!

26:47.690 --> 26:48.815
(DOOR SLAMS CLOSED)

26:49.066 --> 26:50.858
I've got
an English Setter myself,

26:50.943 --> 26:53.278
so I don't cotton
to dog killers.

26:53.362 --> 26:56.406
Trouble is,
poisoning a dog
is just a fine.

26:57.116 --> 26:59.701
But if he's unemployed,
he got to have money

26:59.785 --> 27:01.369
or we'll bust him
for vagrancy.

27:01.453 --> 27:04.205
We'll give him
a full-body strip search.

27:05.791 --> 27:07.750
Jerk a knot
in his tail.

27:08.460 --> 27:09.794
All right.

27:11.088 --> 27:14.882
They got so many ways
on the books to lean
on an undesirable.

27:15.384 --> 27:17.135
He'll feel about
as welcome around here

27:17.219 --> 27:18.344
as a case
of yellow fever.

27:18.429 --> 27:19.637
OFFICER 1: Hands
against the wall.

27:19.722 --> 27:21.931
Spread them.
Spread them.

27:22.016 --> 27:24.017
That him?
OFFICER 2: Face the wall.

27:24.560 --> 27:25.893
One-way mirror,
Mr. Bowden.

27:25.978 --> 27:27.520
He doesn't
know you're here.

27:27.604 --> 27:29.397
Yeah. Yeah, that's him.

27:29.648 --> 27:31.316
Get the shirt off.

27:32.609 --> 27:34.068
Come on, hurry up.

27:34.153 --> 27:36.154
Let's go.
Just pass it
over to him.

27:38.407 --> 27:39.949
Hand it to me.

27:40.034 --> 27:41.534
All right.
Knock off the shoes.

27:42.786 --> 27:45.079
Hand them to
the other officer.

27:46.749 --> 27:49.083
Pass them to him.
Come on, come on.

27:51.378 --> 27:53.629
All right.
Let's put the arms out.

27:53.714 --> 27:55.590
Put your arms
out straight.

27:57.176 --> 27:59.635
Roll your palms.
OFFICER 2:
Do what he says.

28:03.015 --> 28:04.682
OFFICER 1:
Turn around, slow.

28:11.565 --> 28:13.232
(SCOFFS)

28:13.776 --> 28:16.861
I don't know whether
to look at him
or read him.

28:20.324 --> 28:21.741
OFFICER 1:
Stand still.

28:24.286 --> 28:27.163
OFFICER 2:
One more step for you.
You know the routine.

28:29.124 --> 28:30.792
Against the wall.

28:31.460 --> 28:34.879
We searched his apartment.
His car registration
and everything's in order.

28:34.963 --> 28:38.549
There's no guns or
any other weapons.
But we found these.

28:41.136 --> 28:43.054
ELGART: Cady's
savings account.

28:43.806 --> 28:44.931
$30,000?

28:45.682 --> 28:47.892
Yeah, well, see,
his mother died
while he was serving

28:47.976 --> 28:50.061
and the farm
got sold off.
He got the proceeds.

28:50.312 --> 28:53.231
Well, he's got money.
Where does that leave us?

28:53.315 --> 28:55.066
ELGART: Well,
at the very least,
we nail him for the dog.

28:55.150 --> 28:56.192
Now, what happened?

28:56.485 --> 28:58.027
You let the dog out.
Cady abducted him.

28:58.112 --> 28:59.153
No.

29:00.489 --> 29:02.365
We didn't
let the dog out.

29:03.575 --> 29:04.617
Cady came
into your house?

29:04.701 --> 29:06.452
That's illegal entry
with intent.

29:06.537 --> 29:09.747
Yeah. But he didn't
come in the house.

29:10.999 --> 29:14.669
Look, I'm not a cop.
I don't know exactly
how he did it.

29:14.753 --> 29:17.213
I just know that
he did it somehow.

29:17.589 --> 29:19.465
That's not good enough,
Mr. Bowden.

29:19.550 --> 29:21.676
Now, you're a lawyer.
You damn well know that.

29:21.760 --> 29:23.428
OFFICER 1:
Get off the pants.

29:28.809 --> 29:30.309
Sooner or later,
he's gonna screw up.

29:30.394 --> 29:32.019
I mean, the sheriff
assured me

29:32.104 --> 29:34.105
that they always do.
He's an ex-con.

29:34.189 --> 29:36.691
And then he's going
to get the message
in no uncertain terms.

29:36.775 --> 29:38.276
I'd still like
to kill him.

29:40.821 --> 29:42.697
(BAND PLAYING)

29:50.789 --> 29:52.373
(CROWD CHEERING)

30:01.717 --> 30:04.802
Now, Dani, how come
you didn't join up
with them? You can tap.

30:04.887 --> 30:07.013
Yeah, you can do that.
You can tap dance.

30:07.097 --> 30:11.225
I wanted to once,
but I don't know...

30:21.487 --> 30:22.612
Son of a bitch.

30:22.696 --> 30:23.738
What?

30:28.869 --> 30:30.161
He's staring at you.

30:30.245 --> 30:31.496
What are you
talking about?

30:36.627 --> 30:38.377
What the hell
are you doing?

30:38.462 --> 30:40.755
Hot as a firecracker
on the 4th of July.

30:42.841 --> 30:45.051
You're damn lucky
to have her, boy.

30:45.135 --> 30:46.552
You son of a bitch.

30:46.637 --> 30:48.262
Where did he go?

30:48.597 --> 30:49.972
Son of a...

30:54.895 --> 30:57.855
Watch my arm.
Watch my arm.
It might be broke.

30:58.232 --> 30:59.357
What's with you, buddy?

30:59.441 --> 31:01.192
You have no right
to be pushing me
around like that.

31:01.276 --> 31:02.318
I was just
watching the parade.

31:02.402 --> 31:03.486
I wasn't pranking
on nobody.

31:03.570 --> 31:04.946
You son of a bitch!

31:05.030 --> 31:07.365
What are you getting
so upset about?

31:07.741 --> 31:09.200
You're lucky
I don't sue you.

31:11.286 --> 31:12.578
All right.
All right.

31:12.663 --> 31:13.663
MAN: Settle down.

31:13.747 --> 31:15.039
SAM: I am. I am.
I am settled down.

31:17.000 --> 31:18.292
Sam,
what are you doing?

31:18.377 --> 31:19.377
Oh, it's nothing.

31:19.461 --> 31:21.420
Who was that?
It's no one.

31:21.505 --> 31:22.922
Who was that?
No one. Come on.

31:23.006 --> 31:26.133
The fellow with the tie,
his wife took him away.

31:27.302 --> 31:28.678
MAN: I think
he really hurt his arm.

31:28.762 --> 31:29.929
Mom!

31:32.224 --> 31:34.809
LORl: That's an awfully
strong drink you've
got there, mister.

31:34.893 --> 31:36.435
CADY: You said it, boy.
(LAUGHS)

31:36.520 --> 31:40.106
You just put
a little goldfish in it,
and you'll be fine.

31:41.984 --> 31:43.901
You seem to be
having a good time.

31:43.986 --> 31:45.403
I've been practicing.

31:45.487 --> 31:46.862
Practicing for what?

31:47.656 --> 31:48.698
How to fall
on the floor?

31:48.782 --> 31:50.116
A life of debauchery.

31:50.200 --> 31:51.284
"Debauch," what?

31:51.618 --> 31:54.328
Debauchery.
It's a three-syllable word.
Yeah.

31:54.663 --> 31:56.038
(LAUGHING)

31:56.123 --> 31:58.583
Making fun of me?
That's okay. No problem.

31:58.667 --> 31:59.834
No, I'm not. I'm not.

31:59.918 --> 32:00.918
I made you blush.

32:01.003 --> 32:01.961
Blush?

32:02.045 --> 32:05.715
Yes. You're now the color
of your shirt, scarlet.

32:06.174 --> 32:07.383
(CHUCKLES)

32:08.218 --> 32:11.637
I had no business
getting stuck on a guy
who was married.

32:11.722 --> 32:13.306
You certainly did not.

32:13.390 --> 32:14.932
I don't know
what I was thinking.

32:15.017 --> 32:17.018
God only knows.

32:17.185 --> 32:19.604
Now aren't I the bozo
on this bus?

32:20.689 --> 32:24.108
Oh, God. Lest you think
that I slept with
this particular

32:24.234 --> 32:26.110
married guy...
That's your business.
Not mine.

32:26.194 --> 32:27.570
I don't want to
make it sound like

32:27.654 --> 32:28.988
I've been through
a busload of them.

32:29.740 --> 32:32.033
That's the way
it sounded to me.

32:32.326 --> 32:33.409
He was the first.

32:33.493 --> 32:34.535
Oh, yeah.

32:34.620 --> 32:36.078
He was, I swear.

32:36.163 --> 32:37.288
Oh, yeah.

32:37.372 --> 32:39.206
Oh, boy.
Tell it to the judge.

32:39.291 --> 32:41.083
(BOTH LAUGHING)

32:43.086 --> 32:44.629
Actually the rat
stood me up today.

32:44.713 --> 32:45.713
Did he?

32:45.797 --> 32:47.256
Yes!
What a shame.

32:47.341 --> 32:48.549
I know.

32:49.718 --> 32:51.719
So, now it's my turn.
Where are you from?

32:51.803 --> 32:52.887
Where am I from?
Yes.

32:52.971 --> 32:54.972
You're gonna love this.
Yes.

32:55.057 --> 32:59.352
I'm from
the Georgia State
Correctional Facility.

32:59.686 --> 33:01.228
(LAUGHING HYSTERICALLY)

33:06.401 --> 33:08.027
Now you think I'm joking?
That's the truth.

33:08.111 --> 33:09.487
I just got released
from prison.

33:09.738 --> 33:13.366
Oh, my God.
This is the way my day
has been turning out.

33:14.785 --> 33:16.994
Actually,
it reminds me
of a joke.

33:17.746 --> 33:19.205
Do you want
to hear it?
Tell me.

33:19.289 --> 33:20.790
Liven up the night.
All right.

33:21.458 --> 33:24.001
An unmarried woman...

33:24.086 --> 33:25.711
Wait a minute,
that's not it.
An unmarried woman...

33:25.796 --> 33:27.380
Come on, get the joke
straight, darling.

33:27.464 --> 33:29.256
Shut up. Shut up.
Let me do it.

33:29.341 --> 33:31.217
An unmarried woman,
she meets a guy

33:31.301 --> 33:34.178
and he tells her
he just got out
of prison.

33:34.262 --> 33:36.013
"What did you do?"
She asks.

33:36.098 --> 33:38.849
"I hacked my wife
into 52 pieces
with a chain saw."

33:38.934 --> 33:40.267
(LAUGHS LOUDLY)

33:41.436 --> 33:44.146
She says,
"So, you're single?"

33:45.273 --> 33:46.899
That's even funnier.
Thank you.

33:47.984 --> 33:49.318
Could I ask you
something?
What?

33:49.444 --> 33:51.028
What did you do?
I knew you were
going to ask that.

33:51.613 --> 33:53.656
I hacked my wife
into 52 pieces.

33:53.740 --> 33:55.741
I was afraid you were
gonna say that.

33:56.451 --> 33:59.120
Well, I'm a very
small person,
so maybe...

33:59.204 --> 34:01.706
Maybe I can hack you
into 40 pieces.

34:01.790 --> 34:03.249
(BOTH LAUGHING)

34:06.586 --> 34:07.712
What did you do,
really?

34:07.796 --> 34:09.797
"No, really,
but what did you do?"

34:11.882 --> 34:16.094
No, I just...
There was this protest march
on this nuclear power plant,

34:16.179 --> 34:18.723
and so when they came
to arrest us,

34:18.806 --> 34:21.391
this macho sheriff
got a tad rough with
the lady behind me,

34:21.476 --> 34:23.476
so, I popped
the little bastard,

34:23.562 --> 34:25.312
so they gave me
a little time for it.

34:26.732 --> 34:29.692
I'm drinking a Sea Breeze.
I hope you can afford them.

34:29.775 --> 34:30.943
But you gotta
stay sober.

34:31.027 --> 34:34.071
If you ain't sober,
then you're taking
your chances.

34:34.156 --> 34:36.157
Because I'm just
one hell of an animal.

34:36.324 --> 34:38.199
Yeah? Do tell.

34:40.328 --> 34:43.873
Get you on
this side, doll.
Let's do this.

34:43.956 --> 34:45.666
Who is Loretta anyway?

34:45.751 --> 34:48.127
That's the love of my life.
She's no longer with us.

34:48.210 --> 34:49.420
I thought
I was the love
of your life.

34:49.504 --> 34:52.380
Chopped her up
into 52 pieces.

34:52.466 --> 34:53.882
(LAUGHING)

34:57.471 --> 34:58.554
He hurt you like this,
that married guy?

34:58.638 --> 34:59.638
No.

34:59.723 --> 35:00.765
He hurt you like this?

35:00.849 --> 35:03.100
I told you,
we never did anything.

35:03.185 --> 35:04.602
He hurt you like this?

35:04.686 --> 35:06.771
Oh, scandal.

35:06.855 --> 35:08.481
He's a rough one.

35:08.940 --> 35:10.524
How's this feel?

35:13.403 --> 35:16.197
Oh, my God.
Am I under arrest?

35:18.492 --> 35:20.201
Not quite, darling.

35:20.285 --> 35:21.619
(CONTINUES LAUGHING)

35:22.788 --> 35:26.040
Officer, I swear,
it's all a mistake.

35:28.627 --> 35:30.920
That married guy
hurt you like this?

35:31.004 --> 35:33.547
Because what he did to me
hurt a lot worse than this!

35:33.673 --> 35:34.799
(SCREAMS)

35:34.883 --> 35:35.925
No!

35:43.058 --> 35:44.975
I've got you now,
bitch!

35:46.269 --> 35:48.103
(LORI SCREAMING)

35:52.108 --> 35:53.567
(PIANO KEY THUDDING)

35:56.071 --> 35:57.655
Dani, when did
this key stop working?

35:58.573 --> 36:00.741
What? Oh, I don't know.

36:02.786 --> 36:04.703
No wonder.
A wire's missing.

36:07.207 --> 36:08.249
A piano wire
is missing.

36:08.333 --> 36:10.292
Was somebody
fooling around
with the piano?

36:10.377 --> 36:11.418
What?
(TELEPHONE RINGING)

36:13.964 --> 36:15.422
Yeah?
ELGART ON PHONE:
Mr. Bowden.

36:15.841 --> 36:18.092
I think
we might could have
a little break here.

36:18.176 --> 36:19.218
SAM: Good. Good.

36:19.302 --> 36:21.679
I can be there
in a half hour.

36:21.763 --> 36:22.972
All right, fine.
Thank you.

36:23.473 --> 36:24.723
LEIGH: Who was that?

36:24.808 --> 36:26.058
Cady raped another girl.

36:28.353 --> 36:30.104
Rape? I thought
you said it was battery.

36:30.188 --> 36:33.023
Well, yeah,
the case was wobbly.
I got it reduced.

36:33.108 --> 36:35.442
Oh, I remember
those days,
old slippery Sam.

36:35.527 --> 36:38.946
I'm sorry, Leigh.
I just didn't want
to alarm you or Dani.

36:39.030 --> 36:40.197
Why? How old
was that girl?

36:40.282 --> 36:41.448
Sixteen.

36:41.950 --> 36:43.242
Sixteen, what?

36:50.083 --> 36:52.293
Well, my birthday
is coming up.

36:52.711 --> 36:54.378
Neighbors heard screams
and called us.

36:54.462 --> 36:57.298
When the perp drove off,
somebody made his plate.

36:57.382 --> 36:59.383
Max Cady.
Good. Great.

36:59.467 --> 37:02.678
We got one bitty problem.
The girl is scared.

37:02.762 --> 37:05.556
She's claiming
she fell down
some stairs.

37:11.855 --> 37:12.980
Sam.

37:14.274 --> 37:17.318
(SOBBING) Don't...
Don't look at me.

37:19.654 --> 37:20.988
Oh, my God.

37:22.157 --> 37:24.158
You two know
each other?

37:26.620 --> 37:27.870
(LORI SOBBING)

37:28.538 --> 37:30.456
Yeah, we work together.

37:31.499 --> 37:33.083
I'll be outside.

37:37.088 --> 37:38.797
I'm so stupid.

37:38.882 --> 37:40.132
Oh, Lori, don't.

37:44.596 --> 37:47.431
You stood me up
at the club
the other day.

37:48.516 --> 37:50.476
And then
you didn't call.

37:52.562 --> 37:57.566
And by last night,
I was feeling
pretty reckless.

37:59.194 --> 38:01.904
I thought about
what you said,
you know,

38:01.988 --> 38:05.991
that your wife,
she didn't know
I existed.

38:07.452 --> 38:11.455
And I felt like
I was going
to show you.

38:11.581 --> 38:12.706
(SOBBING)

38:13.500 --> 38:16.418
I guess I showed you,
all right, didn't I?

38:18.004 --> 38:20.339
I guess
I really showed you.

38:25.095 --> 38:27.805
Lori, listen to me,
okay?

38:28.723 --> 38:33.978
Now, look, this guy Cady,
he's done this kind
of thing before.

38:35.188 --> 38:38.607
Now, he's going to
do this over
and over again

38:38.692 --> 38:42.027
unless you testify and
we take him to court...

38:42.112 --> 38:43.278
No. No. No.

38:43.363 --> 38:45.948
And press charges
and testify.

38:46.032 --> 38:47.825
Lori.
Sam.

38:47.909 --> 38:52.287
Sam, I know,
I know how it works.
I see it every day.

38:53.248 --> 38:55.916
Only this time,
I'm on the other side.

38:57.002 --> 39:00.629
I don't want to
explain why I was
in a bar

39:00.714 --> 39:04.216
and how much
I had to drink and
what I was wearing.

39:04.300 --> 39:06.593
Not by the people
I work with.

39:06.678 --> 39:10.848
Not by the guys that
I see cross-examine
other people on the stand,

39:10.932 --> 39:15.686
just crucify them
and just laugh
about it later.

39:17.272 --> 39:19.440
They'll even ask
about you.

39:21.234 --> 39:24.194
Lori, listen to me.
I don't care about that.

39:24.279 --> 39:26.405
Well, I care about that.

39:27.741 --> 39:29.575
I'm sure you do, too.

39:30.869 --> 39:32.077
I'm...

39:32.954 --> 39:36.415
I'm terribly sorry, Lori.
I'm just terribly sorry.

39:39.961 --> 39:40.961
ELGART: Look.

39:42.047 --> 39:43.589
If all this is
something personal

39:43.673 --> 39:45.215
between you and
the girl and Cady...

39:45.300 --> 39:46.800
Personal? I mean...

39:47.802 --> 39:49.178
All right, come on,
Lieutenant.

39:49.262 --> 39:50.512
All right.
What are you implying?

39:50.597 --> 39:52.014
Only that there
are some things

39:52.098 --> 39:54.016
that are better
handled quietly.

39:54.100 --> 39:55.768
Not by the police.
(LAUGHS)

39:56.603 --> 39:58.562
This Cady guy
is planning to
rape my wife,

39:58.646 --> 39:59.813
but it's not
your problem anymore?

40:00.148 --> 40:02.399
I can't bust someone
for planning to
rape your wife.

40:02.484 --> 40:04.985
You're a lawyer, Mr. Bowden.
You know that damn well.

40:05.320 --> 40:07.321
Thanks all the same.
The way I'd handle it...

40:07.405 --> 40:09.573
What,
file a restraining order?
I already did.

40:09.657 --> 40:11.742
Just think of
this fellow Cady
as a tiger.

40:11.993 --> 40:14.161
The trick is to
get him out
of the brush.

40:14.245 --> 40:15.704
Now how do we
do that?

40:15.914 --> 40:18.624
You stake out
a couple of your goats
and hide in a tree.

40:18.708 --> 40:20.000
What are you suggesting,
Lieutenant?

40:20.585 --> 40:23.587
That I use
my family as bait?
And then what?

40:23.671 --> 40:25.756
What? I'm gonna hope
that this psychopath

40:25.840 --> 40:27.591
attacks my wife
and child?

40:27.675 --> 40:29.259
And then what?
Blow his head off?

40:29.344 --> 40:30.385
I'm a law officer.

40:31.137 --> 40:33.764
It would be
unethical of me
to advise a citizen

40:33.848 --> 40:35.849
to take the law
into his own hands.

40:35.934 --> 40:38.352
So, I suppose you must've
misunderstood me.

40:38.436 --> 40:39.853
Oh, I guess I must've.

40:40.688 --> 40:43.148
Well, pardon me
all over the place.

41:09.134 --> 41:12.386
And he's been
harassing my family,
but he's clever.

41:12.762 --> 41:15.347
I mean, cleverly,
so that the law
can't touch him.

41:15.431 --> 41:17.141
Also I believe
that he's able to slip

41:17.225 --> 41:18.892
into the house
and out undetected.

41:18.977 --> 41:20.644
Although, is he out?
I can't tell.

41:20.728 --> 41:23.522
He's either out
or he's in.
I'm not sure.

41:23.606 --> 41:25.107
Well, I can't
see through walls,
Mr. Bowden.

41:25.191 --> 41:28.777
I'm not asking you
to see through walls.
That's fine.

41:28.987 --> 41:30.863
I mean,
why can't anybody
do anything for me?

41:30.947 --> 41:32.906
What good are cops
and laws...

41:32.991 --> 41:34.741
Sam, Sam, Sam,
calm down.

41:34.826 --> 41:36.660
Let me explain
something to you.

41:36.744 --> 41:39.496
See, the system
is set up to handle
generalized problems

41:39.581 --> 41:41.623
like burglary
and robbery.

41:42.250 --> 41:45.544
But if some lone creep
out there targets you
for some obscure reason,

41:45.628 --> 41:48.964
the system is
slow and skeptical.
It's pathetic even.

41:50.425 --> 41:51.925
What's your connection
with this fellow?

41:52.010 --> 41:53.135
(SIGHS)

41:53.344 --> 41:55.429
I was his lawyer,
his public defender.

41:55.513 --> 41:57.472
But you shafted
him somehow, right?
(LAUGHS)

41:58.433 --> 42:00.350
Well, at least that's
the way he perceives it.
Sam, Sam.

42:00.435 --> 42:03.103
I don't care
what you did.
What did he do?

42:03.563 --> 42:05.689
He raped
a 16-year-old girl.

42:06.816 --> 42:08.400
Do you have a daughter
around sixteen?

42:09.319 --> 42:10.569
She's fifteen.

42:11.529 --> 42:12.613
All right.
Here's the deal.

42:12.697 --> 42:14.156
I'll do a background check
on him,

42:14.240 --> 42:16.283
follow him for about a week
and write you up
a risk assessment.

42:16.367 --> 42:17.618
All right, good.
Great, great.

42:17.702 --> 42:18.702
Now, the cops...

42:18.786 --> 42:20.120
I can find him.

42:20.205 --> 42:21.830
His name's Max Cady.
You already told me.

42:22.040 --> 42:24.249
Just take it easy.
Stay calm.

42:25.043 --> 42:27.836
Now, Dani, you can
just relax because

42:27.921 --> 42:31.632
your daddy has
a private investigator
on the payroll.

42:32.217 --> 42:33.759
Isn't that right?

42:34.636 --> 42:37.638
What's your feeling
about him?
What, Sam Spade?

42:38.014 --> 42:40.474
Mickey Spillane?
Peter Gunn?

42:41.601 --> 42:43.393
Dirty Harry?
Perry Mason?

42:43.478 --> 42:45.062
No, no, no, no.
Perry Mason...

42:45.146 --> 42:46.480
Perry Mason
was a lawyer.

42:46.564 --> 42:48.398
No, the minute
I walked in
this guy's office,

42:48.483 --> 42:49.733
I felt totally relaxed.

42:49.817 --> 42:51.818
I mean, this guy is
totally in charge.

42:51.903 --> 42:53.862
Kersek deals
with these types
for a living.

42:53.947 --> 42:56.073
He looked like
he was going
to enjoy...

42:56.157 --> 42:57.449
(TELEPHONE RINGS)
(ALL GASP)

42:59.035 --> 43:00.744
Yes?
Yeah, it's me.

43:00.828 --> 43:03.205
After you left,
I had this interesting
conversation

43:03.289 --> 43:05.040
with a C.O. Over at
Statesboro prison.

43:05.250 --> 43:07.584
Mmm-hmm.
Seems our man Cady had
a job in the kitchen.

43:07.669 --> 43:08.669
Right.

43:08.753 --> 43:10.295
There was this other
inmate working in there
with him,

43:10.380 --> 43:12.089
he was an obstinate
S. O.B.
Right.

43:12.590 --> 43:13.924
He hated Cady's
cigar smoke

43:14.008 --> 43:16.468
and he was always bitching
and moaning about it.

43:16.552 --> 43:17.719
Well, one day,
they found him

43:17.804 --> 43:19.680
with his neck broke
and his tongue bit off.

43:19.764 --> 43:21.473
Oh, Jesus.
Yeah.

43:21.933 --> 43:23.684
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

43:26.020 --> 43:28.522
KERSEK: They never could
place Cady near the scene
of the accident,

43:28.606 --> 43:31.858
if you want
to call it that,
at least not out loud.

43:32.735 --> 43:36.238
But the parole board,
they kept him in
for another seven years.

43:36.698 --> 43:39.116
Uh-oh.
The subject is on the move.
Get a good night's sleep.

43:40.034 --> 43:41.994
DANIELLE: Who was that?
Our private eye.

43:42.370 --> 43:43.870
I thought
we were relaxed now.

43:46.541 --> 43:47.833
WOMAN ON PHONE:
New Essex County Hospital.

43:47.917 --> 43:51.253
Yes, room 5036, please.

43:51.337 --> 43:52.379
One minute, please.

43:52.463 --> 43:53.588
All right.

43:54.215 --> 43:55.173
LORI ON PHONE: Hello?

43:55.258 --> 43:56.717
Hi, Lori,
it's me, Sam.

43:56.801 --> 43:59.052
Lori, I just
feel God-awful

43:59.137 --> 44:00.470
you got dragged
into this thing.

44:00.555 --> 44:01.638
It's not your fault.

44:01.723 --> 44:04.433
If I had any idea
that Cady would hurt you

44:04.517 --> 44:06.643
to get at me,
I would have warned you.

44:06.728 --> 44:09.646
Yeah, I know. I know.
I'm glad you called.

44:09.731 --> 44:11.398
Yeah. Yeah, well.

44:11.482 --> 44:13.191
I'm so sorry
about this.

44:13.276 --> 44:14.943
I feel the same way.

44:16.738 --> 44:18.989
So, are you
really determined

44:19.073 --> 44:20.657
about moving back
to Connecticut?

44:20.742 --> 44:22.659
Well, I've thought
about it a lot.

44:22.744 --> 44:25.370
I just think it's
probably the best thing.

44:26.080 --> 44:28.832
I thought that
maybe I could
go back to school.

44:29.625 --> 44:32.210
I'm really going
to miss you, though.

44:32.295 --> 44:34.212
Right.
Excuse me, Lori.

44:34.339 --> 44:36.173
You know,
that sounds real good.
Yeah.

44:36.257 --> 44:38.342
That's gonna work out fine.
I'll get right back to you.

44:38.426 --> 44:40.260
Okay. Bye.
All right, bye.

44:44.557 --> 44:47.517
Well, I just don't know
what I hate more,

44:48.144 --> 44:52.939
that insipid tone
or your stupid,
sophomoric infidelities.

44:53.733 --> 44:55.859
Who was that? Huh?

44:56.444 --> 44:57.527
The girl that
got beat up?

44:57.612 --> 44:58.779
Yes,
it was the girl
that got beat up.

44:58.863 --> 45:00.238
Lori Davis.
I already told you.

45:00.323 --> 45:02.574
She works at
the county courthouse.
She's a clerk.

45:02.992 --> 45:05.410
And what?
You're fucking her?

45:06.954 --> 45:08.789
Interesting choice, Sam.

45:08.873 --> 45:10.707
Calling from
our bedroom phone.

45:10.792 --> 45:12.709
You know, Leigh,
why is it that

45:12.794 --> 45:15.087
whenever I have
a private phone
conversation,

45:15.171 --> 45:18.465
you assume that
I'm fucking someone,
huh? Why is that?

45:18.549 --> 45:20.926
That's why
that psychopath
chose her, right?

45:21.010 --> 45:23.095
Yes, yes, that's why
he chose her.

45:23.179 --> 45:25.263
But I'm not
fucking her
in any way.

45:27.600 --> 45:30.477
Well, you sleazy
son of a bitch!

45:30.561 --> 45:31.895
You son of a bitch!
You son of a bitch!

45:31.979 --> 45:33.897
Goddamn you!
You son of a bitch!

45:33.981 --> 45:35.273
Stop it! Leigh!

45:35.733 --> 45:37.734
Dani is
right downstairs.

45:38.861 --> 45:41.196
Oh. Oh, honey,
there's nothing
the matter.

45:41.280 --> 45:43.031
Yeah, I can see, Dad.

45:44.158 --> 45:47.077
LEIGH: I thought
you promised to leave all
that shit behind in Atlanta.

45:47.161 --> 45:48.495
SAM: What shit?

45:49.497 --> 45:50.747
(MUSIC PLAYING ON TV)
(ARGUMENT CONTINUES)

45:54.919 --> 45:56.211
LEIGH: Christ,
what a waste!

45:56.963 --> 45:58.171
The humiliation
we went through

45:58.256 --> 46:00.090
confessing all our
dirty little secrets

46:00.174 --> 46:02.259
in those horrible sessions
with Dr. Hackett.

46:02.343 --> 46:04.594
Yeah. We talked that
one damn incident
to death, didn't we?

46:04.679 --> 46:05.804
Yeah.
Why did you bother?

46:05.888 --> 46:07.222
Because you
asked me to go.

46:07.306 --> 46:08.557
I mean,
why did you bother?

46:08.641 --> 46:10.183
Why did you bother?

46:10.268 --> 46:14.020
Why did you bother
with you and me?
With the marriage?

46:15.648 --> 46:17.983
Uprooting me and Dani?
Moving?

46:18.401 --> 46:19.860
Because that's
what we decided to do!

46:19.986 --> 46:22.070
You said that
you wanted to get out!
You don't get it, do you, Sam?

46:22.155 --> 46:23.280
All right, Leigh.
What is it I don't get?

46:23.364 --> 46:24.489
You just don't get it.

46:24.615 --> 46:26.366
SAM: What...
What don't I get?

46:26.451 --> 46:29.369
LEIGH: Why put us
through all of that!
Why?

46:29.954 --> 46:31.705
Nadine? (SNIFFLING)

46:31.873 --> 46:33.206
It's Dani.

46:34.709 --> 46:35.917
Nothing.

46:37.128 --> 46:39.337
I'm just
losing my mind here.

46:40.756 --> 46:43.091
You don't have
the balls to walk out,

46:43.176 --> 46:44.801
if that's
what you wanted.
Oh, what I wanted?

46:44.886 --> 46:47.429
Like I was going to split,
with you acting
the way you acted.

46:47.513 --> 46:48.889
Acting?
Yeah.

46:48.973 --> 46:52.017
You did some acting.
I don't remember
doing any acting.

46:52.351 --> 46:53.477
Oh, you don't remember
doing any acting?

46:53.561 --> 46:55.270
Well, hey,
let me refresh
your memory.

46:55.354 --> 46:57.522
Do you remember
not taking any work
for three months?

46:57.607 --> 46:59.524
Do you remember that?
You remember not
fixing any meals?

46:59.609 --> 47:01.568
I'm not on
fucking trial here!

47:01.652 --> 47:04.905
Do you remember crying
every goddamn morning,
afternoon, every evening?

47:04.989 --> 47:06.740
Do you remember that?

47:09.827 --> 47:11.453
I scared you, huh?

47:12.747 --> 47:14.748
What did you think, Sam?

47:15.500 --> 47:18.668
What did you think?
You thought maybe I was
going to kill myself?

47:18.753 --> 47:20.420
Over you?
Who else?

47:20.505 --> 47:21.630
You pompous ass.

47:21.714 --> 47:23.465
Oh, God damn it, Leigh,
who knew what
you were gonna do?

47:23.591 --> 47:24.633
You wouldn't
leave the bedroom!

47:24.717 --> 47:26.468
Yeah. I wish you
could say the same.

47:26.552 --> 47:29.429
Now, look, isn't this
what Dr. Hackett
talked about?

47:29.514 --> 47:31.264
Digging up the past.

47:34.101 --> 47:35.435
I mean,
the relevant issue here

47:35.520 --> 47:37.437
is whether I've been
messing around
in New Essex.

47:37.522 --> 47:39.105
And I have not been.

47:39.190 --> 47:42.526
As far as this girl goes,
Lori, she's just a kid.

47:42.610 --> 47:43.985
Well,
that shouldn't stop you.

47:44.403 --> 47:45.570
She's a baby.

47:45.655 --> 47:47.030
I mean, you know
when you gravitate
to people

47:47.114 --> 47:48.198
in the same world
as you...

47:48.282 --> 47:49.866
You gravitate to women.

47:49.951 --> 47:51.284
Oh, come on, Leigh,
for Christ sake,

47:51.369 --> 47:53.453
I'm a lawyer,
she's a clerk.
She looks up to me.

47:53.538 --> 47:56.331
She's just infatuated.
I can't help that.

48:00.503 --> 48:01.711
(SIGHS)

48:01.796 --> 48:03.755
Look, Leigh,
I'm scared.

48:04.465 --> 48:06.800
I think this
whole thing has...

48:08.719 --> 48:12.722
I keep feeling that
there is some animal
out there stalking us.

48:12.807 --> 48:15.767
I think he wants
to hurt us
in the worst way

48:16.811 --> 48:19.437
and that's got me
frightened to death.

48:23.859 --> 48:25.277
You really are scared,
aren't you?

48:25.361 --> 48:26.736
Yeah.

48:26.821 --> 48:28.947
Somebody finally
got to you.

48:30.491 --> 48:32.826
Look, Leigh,
I think...

48:32.910 --> 48:34.953
I think that this guy
beat and raped her

48:35.037 --> 48:38.039
because he knew that
she wouldn't testify,

48:38.124 --> 48:40.667
that she wouldn't
press charges,

48:40.751 --> 48:42.836
because she knows
the system.

48:42.920 --> 48:44.588
I mean,
she works in it.

48:44.672 --> 48:47.090
She knows that
she'd be on trial.

48:49.010 --> 48:52.470
And then, because
she wouldn't testify,
you would assume that

48:52.555 --> 48:55.932
there was something
going on between us

48:56.017 --> 48:57.934
and it would
cause a rift.

49:00.980 --> 49:03.773
That we'd be much more
vulnerable to him.

49:10.323 --> 49:11.740
I'm glad we talked
about this,

49:11.824 --> 49:13.908
because now
we can work together.

49:14.285 --> 49:15.452
We can beat that
son of a bitch,

49:15.536 --> 49:18.872
the two of us together,
working as a team.

49:20.041 --> 49:21.416
(GROANS)

49:21.834 --> 49:23.335
Jesus Christ.

49:23.711 --> 49:27.130
Oh, yeah, this is great.
This is something else.

49:27.214 --> 49:28.798
Oh. Oh.

49:29.717 --> 49:30.717
Oh, shit!

49:41.687 --> 49:43.146
Here you go.

49:43.230 --> 49:44.481
I'm sorry,
I haven't ordered yet.

49:44.565 --> 49:47.692
That fellow over there
sent this over,
paid for and all.

49:47.777 --> 49:48.860
Who?

49:49.320 --> 49:50.320
Which one?

49:50.404 --> 49:52.113
That guy who
is just leaving.

49:52.490 --> 49:53.490
(SIGHS)

49:55.743 --> 49:56.785
Excuse me.

49:57.828 --> 49:59.788
Hey. Cady, come here.

50:00.665 --> 50:02.290
Wait up a second.

50:02.541 --> 50:05.835
I've been in
a real bad mood lately.
Shame, ain't it?

50:05.920 --> 50:07.170
You know what you can do
to brighten my mood?

50:08.673 --> 50:10.423
No.
Get the hell
out of here.

50:11.425 --> 50:12.467
I don't mean just
this whole town,

50:12.551 --> 50:14.344
I mean the whole
goddamn state.

50:14.428 --> 50:16.096
I don't want to see you,
I don't want to hear you

50:16.180 --> 50:18.056
and I don't want
to smell you.
Now, leave.

50:18.516 --> 50:20.183
I like...
Are you my friend?

50:20.601 --> 50:21.893
No, I'm not your friend.

50:22.395 --> 50:24.187
Oh. 'Cause I thought
maybe you were my friend

50:24.271 --> 50:26.439
because I like
to plan my comings
and goings with friends.

50:26.524 --> 50:27.691
But if you're
not my friend,

50:27.775 --> 50:28.817
and you're planning
my comings and goings,

50:28.901 --> 50:29.984
I'd call that
presumptuous.

50:30.069 --> 50:32.237
In fact, I'd call it
downright rude,

50:32.321 --> 50:33.947
because I ain't
your porch-baby, buddy.

50:34.198 --> 50:36.825
Gee golly gosh.
I sure am sorry
I offended you,

50:36.909 --> 50:38.785
you white trash
piece of shit.

50:39.078 --> 50:41.746
Ooh-ooh. I got
the all-over fidgets
on that one.

50:41.831 --> 50:44.582
You've really shaken me up.
I'm shivering all over.

50:45.334 --> 50:46.501
Ooh.

50:46.794 --> 50:49.921
It's not necessary to
lay a foul tongue
on me, my friend.

50:50.005 --> 50:53.550
I could get upset.
Things could get
out of hand.

50:53.884 --> 50:56.636
And then, in self-defense,
I could do something to you

50:56.721 --> 50:58.388
that you would not like,
right here.

50:58.472 --> 51:00.515
Anytime you
feel squirrelly,
you just jump.

51:00.599 --> 51:04.519
You threatening me?

51:04.979 --> 51:06.354
You catch on fast.

51:07.064 --> 51:08.398
'Cause I'm well
within my rights

51:08.482 --> 51:09.941
to be here
and you know it.

51:10.025 --> 51:11.818
If I stay here,
what you going to do?

51:11.902 --> 51:14.070
I don't give a rat's ass
about your rights.

51:14.155 --> 51:16.406
You just watch your step,
and you know what
I'm talking about.

51:16.490 --> 51:18.158
What are you gonna do?
Arrest me?

51:18.242 --> 51:20.076
You a cop?
Or were you a cop?

51:20.161 --> 51:22.328
Or were you not good enough
to remain on the force?

51:22.413 --> 51:24.456
'Cause, you know
that's the feeling
I'm getting here.

51:27.168 --> 51:29.502
Hope you enjoyed
your breakfast.

51:38.095 --> 51:39.262
Ma'am,
this belong to you?

51:39.346 --> 51:40.305
LEIGH: Can I help you?

51:40.389 --> 51:41.723
I just found it.

51:42.224 --> 51:44.434
I thought you
might need it back.

51:44.518 --> 51:46.728
Not to frighten you,
but if a dogcatcher

51:46.812 --> 51:48.396
comes across a dog
without a license,

51:48.481 --> 51:49.606
he's liable to
think he's a stray

51:49.690 --> 51:52.317
and do God knows
what to it.

51:52.860 --> 51:56.362
You know,
our dog is...

51:57.448 --> 51:58.615
He passed away.

51:58.699 --> 52:00.033
Oh, what a shame.
Yeah.

52:00.117 --> 52:02.577
Man's best friend and all.
Woman's, too.

52:04.455 --> 52:06.748
Even without
closing my eyes,
I can picture him,

52:06.832 --> 52:10.794
big, friendly, shaggy,
asleep at your feet,

52:10.878 --> 52:12.587
keeping you company
while you're trying

52:12.671 --> 52:15.715
to finish up those
pesky little sketches.

52:18.844 --> 52:21.179
Oh, you're Max Cady,
aren't you?

52:23.516 --> 52:27.227
You know, you better
get the hell out of here
before I call the police.

52:27.311 --> 52:29.020
I'm not doing nothing.

52:29.104 --> 52:30.438
Just giving you back
your dog collar.

52:30.523 --> 52:31.773
I'm not on
your property.

52:31.857 --> 52:33.983
Oh, what'd you
come out here for,
you want to look around?

52:34.068 --> 52:36.152
Go ahead, Mr. Cady,
take a good look.

52:37.071 --> 52:38.238
Nice house.
Yeah.

52:38.322 --> 52:41.241
It is a nice house.
You satisfied
now you've seen it?

52:42.910 --> 52:45.078
Or is there more? Huh?

52:46.163 --> 52:47.539
Is that it?

52:47.623 --> 52:49.999
There is going to
be more, isn't there,
Mr. Cady? Huh?

52:50.084 --> 52:52.460
You won't stop
until you're happy.

52:53.045 --> 52:56.172
How can I be happy, Leigh,
when you're not happy?

52:57.258 --> 52:59.217
You don't know
anything about me.

52:59.301 --> 53:00.510
I know what I see,
ma'am.

53:00.594 --> 53:01.594
Yeah?
Mmm-hmm.

53:03.764 --> 53:05.473
I wanted to know
what you looked like.

53:05.558 --> 53:07.141
I've been waiting
to see your face,

53:07.226 --> 53:09.060
but you know now
that I see you,

53:10.771 --> 53:12.647
you are just repulsive.

53:13.065 --> 53:14.357
I understand.
Yeah.

53:14.441 --> 53:16.359
I'm not your type.
No.

53:16.443 --> 53:18.695
All that prison time
made me coarse.

53:18.779 --> 53:21.614
Guess I'm covered in
too many tattoos, huh?

53:21.991 --> 53:23.700
But, you see,
there's not a whole
hell of a lot

53:23.784 --> 53:27.245
to do in prison but
desecrate your flesh.

53:27.621 --> 53:29.539
Of course it didn't
have to be that way
for either of us

53:29.623 --> 53:32.333
if your husband
hadn't betrayed us both.

53:33.085 --> 53:35.044
Who knows?
We might have been
different people.

53:35.129 --> 53:37.505
We might have
been happy, Leigh.

53:38.215 --> 53:39.799
Mom, someone's
on the phone!

53:39.884 --> 53:41.009
Dani!

53:41.802 --> 53:42.927
Don't come out here!

53:46.098 --> 53:47.599
(TIRES SCREECHING)

53:53.147 --> 53:55.940
Sam. Hey, Sam.
Yo, Sam.

53:57.151 --> 53:58.651
Sam, I thought
I'd catch you here.

54:00.070 --> 54:01.863
Well, that little
smart aleck made me.

54:01.947 --> 54:02.947
He what?

54:03.032 --> 54:04.032
Well, it wasn't
my fault.

54:04.116 --> 54:05.366
He was looking
to be covered.

54:05.451 --> 54:07.201
You're right. There is
a lot of cutsie-cutsie

54:07.286 --> 54:08.369
in that little prick,
isn't there?

54:08.454 --> 54:09.454
Yeah, I told you.

54:09.538 --> 54:10.663
You know
where he was today?

54:10.748 --> 54:13.833
At the public library reading
Thus Spake Zarathustra

54:13.918 --> 54:16.044
by Friedrich Nietzsche,
he's this German philosopher.

54:16.128 --> 54:17.253
He said that
God is dead.

54:17.338 --> 54:18.421
God is dead. Right.

54:18.505 --> 54:20.173
Look, we can keep
going this way,

54:20.257 --> 54:22.383
but it's going to get
awful expensive, Sam.

54:23.928 --> 54:25.637
Well, look, I'm not so
concerned about days.

54:25.721 --> 54:27.513
Just stay on him
a few more nights,
will you?

54:27.598 --> 54:29.682
Look, do you really want
to resolve this situation?

54:30.559 --> 54:31.893
Yes, I'd love
to resolve it.

54:31.977 --> 54:33.144
Then I got
a suggestion.

54:34.438 --> 54:36.522
There's men that
can be hired, by me,

54:36.607 --> 54:38.608
to do a little job on Cady,
a little hospital job.

54:42.988 --> 54:44.656
What are we
talking about here?

54:44.740 --> 54:46.366
Two pieces of pipe
and a bicycle chain.

54:48.327 --> 54:49.452
Sam.

54:50.037 --> 54:51.371
He won't be
so scary after that.

54:51.455 --> 54:52.497
I'm a lawyer, right?

54:52.623 --> 54:53.706
We agree that
I'm a lawyer?
Yeah.

54:54.249 --> 54:55.541
You know,
maybe 2,000 years ago,

54:55.584 --> 54:57.877
we'd have taken this guy out
and stoned him to death.
(STARTS ENGINE)

54:57.962 --> 55:01.297
I can't operate
outside the law.
The law is my business.

55:06.387 --> 55:09.430
SAM: Hi, I'm home!
Where is everybody?

55:09.515 --> 55:10.640
In here.

55:12.017 --> 55:15.103
Evening, ladies.
Oh, chicken.

55:17.272 --> 55:19.148
How is everything?
Is everything okay?

55:19.233 --> 55:21.025
DANIELLE: Yeah.
Good. Good.

55:26.073 --> 55:27.740
(WHISPERING)
He was here today.

55:32.746 --> 55:34.080
(TELEPHONE RINGING)

55:35.499 --> 55:36.624
DANIELLE: Hello?

55:36.709 --> 55:37.792
MAN ON PHONE:
Hello, Danielle?

55:38.419 --> 55:39.752
Is this
Miss Danielle Bowden?

55:39.837 --> 55:40.920
Yeah.

55:41.213 --> 55:43.172
This is your
new teacher calling.

55:43.257 --> 55:44.674
From English or Drama?

55:44.758 --> 55:45.800
Drama.

55:46.593 --> 55:47.593
So how you doing?

55:47.678 --> 55:48.678
Fine.

55:49.013 --> 55:50.805
Well, I'm just
going down the list,

55:50.931 --> 55:52.807
greeting my
summer students.

55:53.267 --> 55:55.101
You sound kind of down.

55:55.185 --> 55:56.352
No.

55:57.563 --> 56:00.523
There's just been stuff
going on around here,
that's all.

56:00.607 --> 56:02.233
I see.
Anything I can do?

56:02.317 --> 56:03.526
I doubt it.

56:03.610 --> 56:06.779
I mean,
shit happens, you know,
like the T-shirt says.

56:06.864 --> 56:07.947
Yeah.

56:09.199 --> 56:13.244
Well, you know, Danielle,
all that negativity,
you can use that.

56:14.997 --> 56:16.581
What do you mean?

56:16.665 --> 56:18.458
Well, I'm the kind
of teacher that takes

56:18.542 --> 56:20.251
a very personal interest
in his kids.

56:20.335 --> 56:21.961
And don't mind me if
I tell you everything

56:22.046 --> 56:24.839
you're going through,
it's okay, go with it.

56:24.923 --> 56:26.049
The awkwardness
you feel, say,

56:26.133 --> 56:27.216
when you're walking
down the street

56:27.301 --> 56:30.553
and some leering fool
is making fun
of your sexuality,

56:30.637 --> 56:32.555
the turmoil you feel,
extra bad when

56:32.639 --> 56:34.724
that particular time
of the month
comes around,

56:34.808 --> 56:37.018
the anger you feel
that your mom and dad

56:37.102 --> 56:38.311
won't let you
just grow up

56:38.395 --> 56:40.563
and be yourself,
be a woman.

56:40.981 --> 56:42.899
Go with it.
Don't suppress
or deny it.

56:42.983 --> 56:45.443
Use it in your life
and your work.

56:47.196 --> 56:48.988
Okay. I mean...

56:49.990 --> 56:52.992
That's... I'll have to
think about all that.

56:54.244 --> 56:58.081
So, class is tomorrow
in Room 110, right?

56:59.249 --> 57:01.417
No, it's been changed
to the theater.

57:01.502 --> 57:03.461
I mean, what better place
for drama, right?

57:03.545 --> 57:04.837
Yeah.

57:06.715 --> 57:08.174
And remember, Danielle,

57:08.258 --> 57:11.552
you can use all those fears
to draw upon and learn.

57:12.888 --> 57:14.931
You know
this little tune?

57:15.265 --> 57:16.557
WOMAN ON TAPE: (SINGING)
If you want a

57:16.642 --> 57:23.189
Do-right-all-day woman

57:24.817 --> 57:25.942
Woman

57:26.360 --> 57:33.366
You've got to be
a do-right-all-night man

57:35.452 --> 57:36.702
Man
(DANIELLE GIGGLES)

57:37.287 --> 57:41.457
Now, you can trust in me,
because I'm a do-right man,
okay?

57:43.836 --> 57:45.211
Okay, 'night now.

57:45.963 --> 57:48.172
Okay. Good night.

57:52.803 --> 57:54.971
You know, honey,
I think maybe
I should walk you in.

57:55.055 --> 57:58.641
No, it's okay, Mom.
There's a lot
of people here.

57:58.725 --> 58:00.810
I'll be right here
at 4:00 to pick you up.

58:00.894 --> 58:02.854
Okay. Bye.
Bye.

58:04.898 --> 58:07.859
I didn't think
summer session was
gonna be so crowded.

58:07.943 --> 58:09.485
It's not.
They're just having
a big meeting

58:09.570 --> 58:11.946
about next fall's
chorus program.

58:12.030 --> 58:13.990
I have to go downstairs
for Drama. Bye.

58:14.074 --> 58:15.408
Okay, bye.

58:16.118 --> 58:17.702
(BELL RINGING)

59:01.288 --> 59:02.455
Hello.

59:07.044 --> 59:08.252
Nadine?

59:21.975 --> 59:25.436
I'm here for
the Drama class.

59:31.777 --> 59:32.777
Hi.

59:33.320 --> 59:34.654
Oops.

59:34.905 --> 59:36.405
Am I busted?

59:36.490 --> 59:38.115
No.
I hope not.

59:38.533 --> 59:41.244
You can't smoke grass
in school.

59:41.328 --> 59:43.496
Privilege of
the profession.

59:44.665 --> 59:47.375
Eases inhibitions.
You down here for Drama?

59:47.459 --> 59:48.542
Yeah.

59:48.835 --> 59:51.170
Are you
the Drama teacher?

59:51.255 --> 59:53.089
And you're,
let me guess.

59:56.426 --> 59:57.510
Cecile James?

59:58.011 --> 01:00:01.597
No, I'm Danielle Bowden.

01:00:02.015 --> 01:00:04.350
Danielle.
Oh, we spoke last night.

01:00:04.768 --> 01:00:05.851
Yeah.

01:00:07.187 --> 01:00:09.188
Oh, I'm sorry.
How rude.

01:00:10.524 --> 01:00:11.649
It's okay.

01:00:12.025 --> 01:00:13.234
Um...

01:00:16.989 --> 01:00:18.990
(SINGING) I think
we're alone now...

01:00:19.116 --> 01:00:20.491
(CHUCKLES)

01:00:23.537 --> 01:00:24.578
Okay.

01:00:31.461 --> 01:00:32.712
(EXHALES)

01:00:36.466 --> 01:00:38.926
Thanks. Here.

01:00:39.553 --> 01:00:41.804
I'm going to
give this to you.

01:00:42.848 --> 01:00:44.265
Ow. (LAUGHS)

01:00:45.976 --> 01:00:48.311
Little trick I learned.
Take it.

01:00:50.564 --> 01:00:53.649
You know when we spoke
on the phone last night?

01:00:53.734 --> 01:00:54.942
Mmm-hmm.

01:00:56.528 --> 01:00:59.071
You really
made sense to me

01:01:00.782 --> 01:01:01.824
and I thought a lot.

01:01:02.659 --> 01:01:04.160
Those are human truths,
darling.

01:01:04.244 --> 01:01:05.411
That's what
it's all about.

01:01:05.495 --> 01:01:07.788
And that's what
we deal with here.

01:01:08.248 --> 01:01:10.583
See the book you have,
Thomas Wolfe?

01:01:11.084 --> 01:01:14.211
It's all about
self-discovery,
the inner voyage.

01:01:15.672 --> 01:01:17.757
I like the end

01:01:18.592 --> 01:01:24.263
where Eugene's journey...
It was really mystical,
you know,

01:01:25.140 --> 01:01:28.059
and it was almost
like a pilgrimage.

01:01:28.935 --> 01:01:31.020
Almost like a cop-out,
if you ask me.

01:01:31.271 --> 01:01:34.190
Although those were
the facts of Wolfe's life.

01:01:35.192 --> 01:01:37.860
The novel is
what you would call
a roman Ã  clef.

01:01:37.944 --> 01:01:39.820
You know what that is?
(SIGHS)

01:01:41.406 --> 01:01:42.615
Sure.

01:01:43.408 --> 01:01:45.034
Well, nonetheless,
you can't escape

01:01:45.118 --> 01:01:46.911
your demons just
by leaving home.

01:01:47.788 --> 01:01:50.998
Although writers
do find new freedom
when they relocate abroad.

01:01:51.083 --> 01:01:54.043
Take Henry Miller.
Have you read
his trilogy?

01:01:54.127 --> 01:01:55.628
Plexus, Nexus
and Sexus?

01:01:57.089 --> 01:01:59.256
No. No.
You haven't
read that?

01:02:00.050 --> 01:02:01.842
You're missing
something.

01:02:02.302 --> 01:02:06.639
Well, you know what?
I did read
Tropic of Cancer.

01:02:07.641 --> 01:02:09.225
Just parts of it,
though,

01:02:09.309 --> 01:02:13.145
because I had to
sneak it off my parents'
shelf, you know?

01:02:13.730 --> 01:02:18.317
But his descriptions
are pretty vivid,
I would say.

01:02:18.985 --> 01:02:21.445
In one of the novels,
I don't recall which,

01:02:21.530 --> 01:02:24.365
he describes an erection
as a piece of lead
with wings on it.

01:02:25.534 --> 01:02:27.159
I didn't read
that part.

01:02:27.244 --> 01:02:28.994
Of course not.
You're not allowed.

01:02:29.079 --> 01:02:31.122
Your parents
don't want you to
achieve adulthood.

01:02:31.206 --> 01:02:32.248
That's natural.

01:02:32.332 --> 01:02:35.501
They know the pitfalls
of adulthood,
all that freedom.

01:02:35.585 --> 01:02:37.628
They know it
only too well.

01:02:38.463 --> 01:02:41.382
Temptation to stray,
deflecting their guilt
and anger onto you

01:02:41.466 --> 01:02:44.927
for a crime that's
not even a crime,
for smoking grass.

01:02:50.684 --> 01:02:52.184
Wait a second.

01:02:53.812 --> 01:02:54.937
Where are you from?

01:02:56.606 --> 01:02:57.648
Where am I from?

01:02:57.732 --> 01:02:59.525
Yeah.
Where do you think
I'm from?

01:03:00.485 --> 01:03:02.111
I don't know, but...

01:03:02.195 --> 01:03:04.488
If I told you,
you going to
get mad at me?

01:03:04.948 --> 01:03:06.031
No.

01:03:12.205 --> 01:03:14.373
I'm from
the black forest.

01:03:18.044 --> 01:03:19.545
That's funny.

01:03:20.714 --> 01:03:23.757
You're not
the Drama teacher,
are you?

01:03:24.718 --> 01:03:26.552
Maybe I'm
the big bad wolf.

01:03:28.680 --> 01:03:29.680
Umm...

01:03:31.308 --> 01:03:34.894
So you're that guy
that's been hanging
around the house?

01:03:35.562 --> 01:03:38.272
You're the one that
killed my mom's dog?

01:03:39.566 --> 01:03:40.733
Your mom's dog
was killed?

01:03:40.817 --> 01:03:41.984
Yeah.

01:03:42.736 --> 01:03:45.321
I didn't even know
anything about that.

01:03:45.405 --> 01:03:46.906
That's a shame.

01:03:47.532 --> 01:03:48.782
That's a damn shame.

01:03:49.743 --> 01:03:51.160
Yes, it was.

01:03:51.453 --> 01:03:53.412
What kind
of dog was it?

01:03:54.206 --> 01:03:56.499
I don't know.
He was just...

01:03:56.583 --> 01:03:58.792
He was fluffy, and...

01:04:00.212 --> 01:04:01.420
Fluffy?

01:04:02.422 --> 01:04:03.881
Mmm-hmm.

01:04:06.301 --> 01:04:08.093
So you didn't do that?

01:04:08.178 --> 01:04:10.262
Of course
I didn't do that.

01:04:15.101 --> 01:04:16.393
Okay.

01:04:16.478 --> 01:04:17.770
I wouldn't do that.

01:04:18.688 --> 01:04:21.357
So why... What are
you doing here, then?

01:04:21.650 --> 01:04:24.860
Well, I came to meet you,
to be honest with you.

01:04:28.740 --> 01:04:29.782
Why? I mean...

01:04:29.866 --> 01:04:30.866
Because

01:04:32.452 --> 01:04:35.871
I wanted to meet you,
see what you're like.

01:04:35.956 --> 01:04:38.958
I see you're
a nice person.
That's all.

01:04:42.462 --> 01:04:43.963
You're not going
to hurt me, are you?

01:04:44.047 --> 01:04:46.048
I'm not going to
hurt you at all.

01:04:46.132 --> 01:04:48.217
There's no
hurting here, Danielle.

01:04:49.678 --> 01:04:51.929
Between us,
there's no anger,
nothing.

01:04:52.013 --> 01:04:54.014
Just a search
for truth.

01:04:55.141 --> 01:04:58.227
I mean, did you judge me,
did you get angry at me

01:04:58.311 --> 01:04:59.979
when you caught me
smoking the grass?

01:05:00.063 --> 01:05:01.188
Hmm?

01:05:01.273 --> 01:05:02.356
No.

01:05:03.817 --> 01:05:05.734
But your parents,
they judged you.

01:05:05.819 --> 01:05:07.945
They got plenty angry
at you, didn't they?

01:05:08.029 --> 01:05:09.238
Yeah.
Mmm-hmm.

01:05:09.823 --> 01:05:12.283
They punished you
for their sins.

01:05:13.326 --> 01:05:14.743
What did they do?

01:05:14.828 --> 01:05:15.995
They...

01:05:17.038 --> 01:05:20.416
My dad...
They just yelled
a whole lot

01:05:20.500 --> 01:05:23.127
and my mom cried

01:05:23.211 --> 01:05:26.755
and my dad said
I couldn't drive
the Cherokee.

01:05:26.840 --> 01:05:29.216
I would say
they punished you
for their sins,

01:05:29.301 --> 01:05:30.634
and you resent that,

01:05:30.719 --> 01:05:32.720
and you should
resent it.

01:05:33.555 --> 01:05:36.849
But Professor do-right has
a little advice for you.

01:05:37.225 --> 01:05:38.767
You shouldn't
damn them.

01:05:38.852 --> 01:05:40.603
Don't judge them.
Just forgive them,

01:05:40.687 --> 01:05:42.730
for they know not
what they do.

01:05:44.357 --> 01:05:45.774
Oh...
Um...

01:05:45.859 --> 01:05:47.109
Why do you
hate my father?

01:05:47.485 --> 01:05:50.863
I don't hate him at all.
Oh, no. I pray for him.

01:05:51.531 --> 01:05:53.324
I'm here to help him.

01:05:53.742 --> 01:05:56.785
I mean, we all
make mistakes,
Danielle.

01:05:57.412 --> 01:06:00.164
You and I have.
But at least we try
to admit it.

01:06:00.540 --> 01:06:01.874
Don't we?

01:06:02.292 --> 01:06:03.459
Yeah.

01:06:03.960 --> 01:06:05.753
But your daddy,
he don't.

01:06:07.380 --> 01:06:11.133
Every man carries
a circle of hell around
his head like a halo.

01:06:11.217 --> 01:06:12.384
Your daddy, too.

01:06:12.510 --> 01:06:17.473
Every man, every man
has to go through hell
to reach his paradise.

01:06:18.266 --> 01:06:20.267
You know
what paradise is?

01:06:20.935 --> 01:06:22.519
No.
Salvation.

01:06:24.064 --> 01:06:26.065
'Cause your daddy's
not happy.

01:06:26.149 --> 01:06:27.566
Your mommy's
not happy.

01:06:28.109 --> 01:06:31.320
And you know what?
You're not happy.

01:06:32.864 --> 01:06:33.989
Are you?

01:06:34.074 --> 01:06:35.199
No, I'm not.

01:06:40.038 --> 01:06:42.039
You thought about me
last night, didn't you?

01:06:42.123 --> 01:06:43.415
(LAUGHS)

01:06:45.460 --> 01:06:46.460
Um...

01:06:47.587 --> 01:06:48.712
Yes, I did.

01:06:49.589 --> 01:06:50.756
I know.

01:06:53.343 --> 01:06:56.720
You know, I think
I might have
found a companion,

01:06:58.056 --> 01:07:00.974
a companion for
that long walk
to the light.

01:07:04.062 --> 01:07:06.480
Do you mind if
I put my arm
around you?

01:07:10.860 --> 01:07:12.027
Um...

01:07:19.994 --> 01:07:21.328
It's okay.

01:07:23.456 --> 01:07:25.124
No, I don't mind.

01:07:26.251 --> 01:07:27.459
Okay.

01:07:41.433 --> 01:07:42.725
(GIGGLES)

01:08:40.992 --> 01:08:42.283
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

01:08:55.548 --> 01:08:57.633
Kersek, where the hell
have you been,
for Christ sake?

01:08:57.716 --> 01:08:59.134
He came at my daughter
at school.

01:08:59.219 --> 01:09:00.260
You asked me to
watch him nights.

01:09:00.345 --> 01:09:02.513
I'm watching him nights.
What happened?

01:09:02.596 --> 01:09:05.140
My wife, Leigh,
she found some marijuana

01:09:05.225 --> 01:09:06.558
in one of
Dani's schoolbooks.

01:09:06.643 --> 01:09:09.478
We don't know if Cady
gave it to her or
exactly what happened,

01:09:09.562 --> 01:09:11.313
but she's scared and
she won't talk about it.

01:09:11.397 --> 01:09:13.732
But now this has
gone far enough.
It's got to stop!

01:09:13.817 --> 01:09:14.817
You phone the cops?

01:09:14.901 --> 01:09:16.401
No, I didn't
phone the cops.

01:09:16.486 --> 01:09:17.653
I mean, what did
you call them?

01:09:17.737 --> 01:09:19.654
You call them "Slow,
skeptical, pathetic, even."

01:09:19.781 --> 01:09:21.573
Dani.
No, Leigh,
that's all right.

01:09:21.658 --> 01:09:23.533
Just hold on a minute.

01:09:25.495 --> 01:09:28.622
Kersek, look,
I want to hire
those three guys,

01:09:28.706 --> 01:09:30.290
you remember,
the hospital job.

01:09:30.375 --> 01:09:33.085
Consider it done,
the sooner the better.

01:09:33.877 --> 01:09:35.546
Three men's going
to cost you a grand.

01:09:35.630 --> 01:09:36.796
Now I know that's
not chicken feed,

01:09:36.881 --> 01:09:38.381
but you don't wanna go
with less than three.

01:09:38.466 --> 01:09:40.509
It's better to
overdo it.

01:09:40.593 --> 01:09:42.386
Okay.
You'll have the money
in the morning.

01:09:42.470 --> 01:09:44.179
All right.
Then we'll be on
for tomorrow night.

01:09:44.264 --> 01:09:47.515
And Sam,
you'll feel good
about this.

01:09:51.270 --> 01:09:52.395
All right.

01:10:05.451 --> 01:10:07.870
Do you notice
these young people?

01:10:07.954 --> 01:10:09.454
They don't
look very happy.

01:10:09.539 --> 01:10:12.165
They're committed
to their professions
and to their ambitions,

01:10:12.250 --> 01:10:13.709
but they're not
committed to each other.

01:10:13.793 --> 01:10:15.794
Cady, shut up
and listen.

01:10:17.255 --> 01:10:19.047
If you don't leave...

01:10:19.507 --> 01:10:21.383
If you don't
leave my family alone

01:10:21.467 --> 01:10:23.594
and if you don't
get out of here,

01:10:23.678 --> 01:10:26.805
you're going to be hurting
like you never dreamed.

01:10:28.766 --> 01:10:29.766
Could you repeat that?

01:10:29.851 --> 01:10:30.893
I said,

01:10:30.977 --> 01:10:33.145
if you don't
get out of here,

01:10:33.229 --> 01:10:35.606
you're going to be hurting
like you never dreamed.

01:10:36.316 --> 01:10:37.900
A threat?
Yeah.

01:10:37.984 --> 01:10:39.735
You bet your ass
that's a threat.

01:10:39.819 --> 01:10:41.778
Well,
I have thought
of relocating

01:10:41.863 --> 01:10:44.907
somewhere where I'd
be more appreciated,
California, perhaps.

01:10:44.991 --> 01:10:47.659
I could teach
earthquake preparedness.

01:10:48.161 --> 01:10:51.705
But then it hits me,
I love New Essex,
Counselor.

01:10:52.957 --> 01:10:55.083
I mean,
where else could
I just casually confer

01:10:55.168 --> 01:10:56.335
with an old colleague?

01:10:56.419 --> 01:10:59.796
We're not colleagues.
Do you understand that?
We're not colleagues.

01:10:59.881 --> 01:11:01.006
Still think you're
better than me.

01:11:01.090 --> 01:11:02.382
No, I don't think
I'm better than you.

01:11:02.467 --> 01:11:03.926
That's not
the goddamned point.

01:11:04.010 --> 01:11:05.886
Good. 'Cause if
you're not better than me,

01:11:05.970 --> 01:11:07.679
then I can have
what you have.

01:11:08.431 --> 01:11:09.514
What do I have?

01:11:09.891 --> 01:11:11.642
A wife, a daughter.

01:11:14.020 --> 01:11:17.189
I'm going to teach you
the meaning of commitment.

01:11:17.523 --> 01:11:19.650
Fourteen years ago,
I was forced to make

01:11:19.734 --> 01:11:21.568
a commitment to
an eight-by-nine cell

01:11:21.653 --> 01:11:24.696
and now you're
going to be forced
to make a commitment.

01:11:24.781 --> 01:11:27.240
You could say I'm here
to save you.

01:11:30.536 --> 01:11:31.620
Fine.

01:11:33.039 --> 01:11:34.873
Check out the Bible,
Counselor,

01:11:34.958 --> 01:11:36.750
the book between
Esther and Psalms.

01:11:43.758 --> 01:11:45.550
Dani? Dani?

01:11:48.012 --> 01:11:49.513
You all right?

01:11:50.473 --> 01:11:51.807
What?
Is everything
all right?

01:11:51.891 --> 01:11:52.975
Yeah.

01:11:56.229 --> 01:11:58.438
This isn't going
to work, you know.

01:11:58.523 --> 01:11:59.982
What isn't going
to work?

01:12:00.233 --> 01:12:02.734
Locking us in,
hiding us from the world.

01:12:03.069 --> 01:12:04.736
Oh, don't be
so dramatic, Dani.

01:12:05.071 --> 01:12:06.655
Making me stay out
of school.

01:12:06.739 --> 01:12:08.657
You're going back
to school tomorrow.

01:12:08.741 --> 01:12:09.866
And put
some clothes on.

01:12:09.951 --> 01:12:11.451
You're not
a little kid anymore.

01:12:11.619 --> 01:12:14.204
Yeah? Then why
am I going back
to school tomorrow?

01:12:14.288 --> 01:12:15.539
What are you
going to do?

01:12:15.623 --> 01:12:18.083
That's none of
your concern, Dani.

01:12:20.169 --> 01:12:24.756
Dad, he didn't
force himself
on me, you know.

01:12:25.717 --> 01:12:27.592
I know you'd like
to think that he did.

01:12:28.845 --> 01:12:30.637
But I think he was...

01:12:31.764 --> 01:12:34.975
I think he was
just trying to make
a connection with me.

01:12:35.268 --> 01:12:36.309
You know?
Now, Dani,

01:12:36.978 --> 01:12:38.437
I want you to
listen to me.

01:12:38.521 --> 01:12:41.106
All right? No.
Do you understand?

01:12:41.607 --> 01:12:45.485
No. There will never
be any connection

01:12:45.570 --> 01:12:48.572
between you
and Max Cady.

01:12:50.158 --> 01:12:51.950
You understand that?

01:13:01.669 --> 01:13:02.794
Did he touch you?

01:13:03.296 --> 01:13:04.463
(CHUCKLES)

01:13:06.132 --> 01:13:09.551
What are you
laughing about?
Why are you smiling?

01:13:09.635 --> 01:13:12.262
I'm asking you a question.
Did he touch you?

01:13:13.514 --> 01:13:15.307
Dani, wipe that
smile off your face!

01:13:15.391 --> 01:13:17.768
I'm asking you,
did he touch you?

01:13:24.567 --> 01:13:26.777
No, no, no, wait, Dani.
I'm sorry.

01:13:27.487 --> 01:13:28.987
No, I'm sorry.

01:13:30.114 --> 01:13:31.948
Wait, honey.
I'm sorry.

01:13:32.033 --> 01:13:34.534
Get out of here!
Get out of here!

01:13:39.791 --> 01:13:40.957
(DOOR CLOSES)

01:13:58.142 --> 01:13:59.309
THUG: Max?

01:13:59.852 --> 01:14:01.186
(GRUNTING)

01:14:40.893 --> 01:14:43.603
Come on.
Come on. Come on.

01:14:43.729 --> 01:14:45.021
Come on.

01:14:46.357 --> 01:14:47.691
(GRUNTING)

01:15:06.460 --> 01:15:07.669
(CLATTERING)

01:15:13.885 --> 01:15:19.264
Counselor?

01:15:20.141 --> 01:15:21.516
Is that you?

01:15:23.019 --> 01:15:24.352
Counselor?

01:15:25.396 --> 01:15:28.315
(SINGSONG VOICE)
Come out, come out,
wherever you are.

01:15:42.872 --> 01:15:44.831
I ain't no white trash
piece of shit.

01:15:44.916 --> 01:15:46.875
I'm better
than you all.

01:15:49.795 --> 01:15:51.546
I can out-learn you.

01:15:53.007 --> 01:15:54.966
I can out-read you.

01:15:55.051 --> 01:15:59.763
I can outthink you,
and I can
out-philosophize you.

01:16:00.056 --> 01:16:02.390
And I'm going
to outlast you.

01:16:02.475 --> 01:16:03.850
You think
a couple of whacks

01:16:03.935 --> 01:16:06.603
to my good-old-boy gut's
gonna get me down?

01:16:07.104 --> 01:16:09.397
It's going to
take a hell of a lot more
than that, Counselor,

01:16:09.482 --> 01:16:11.733
to prove you're
better than me!

01:16:14.070 --> 01:16:18.281
"I am like God,
and God like me.

01:16:18.366 --> 01:16:21.076
"I am as large as God.

01:16:21.160 --> 01:16:24.162
"He is as small as I.

01:16:24.247 --> 01:16:28.583
"He cannot above me
nor I beneath him be."

01:16:30.503 --> 01:16:33.755
Silesius,
17th century.

01:16:38.719 --> 01:16:43.348
Counselor?

01:16:46.018 --> 01:16:51.022
Could you be there?

01:16:52.066 --> 01:16:53.316
(WHISTLES)

01:16:54.568 --> 01:16:55.568
(WHISTLES AGAIN)

01:16:56.445 --> 01:16:57.779
Counselor?

01:17:05.538 --> 01:17:07.455
I wonder
if you're here.

01:17:17.008 --> 01:17:18.216
Fuck it.

01:17:19.593 --> 01:17:22.679
If you're here,
what the fuck's
the difference?

01:17:23.597 --> 01:17:24.848
Fuck it!

01:17:35.192 --> 01:17:36.443
WOMAN: I've got
Mr. Kersek on one.

01:17:36.527 --> 01:17:37.736
SAM: Good.
I'll take it.

01:17:37.820 --> 01:17:38.903
Tom.

01:17:39.822 --> 01:17:41.531
Sam, you look tired.
You get that writ?

01:17:41.615 --> 01:17:44.993
No, no, we got to
get into that.
Let me just grab this.

01:17:45.077 --> 01:17:46.870
Kersek.
Look, I'm damn sorry
about last night.

01:17:46.954 --> 01:17:48.038
That son of a bitch
could survive

01:17:48.122 --> 01:17:49.247
a preemptive
nuclear strike.

01:17:49.332 --> 01:17:50.623
All right.
Hang on a second.
Hang on a second.

01:17:51.125 --> 01:17:53.251
Tom, I'm not doing it.
I pulled a fast one

01:17:53.336 --> 01:17:55.920
and it's come back and
it's bit me on the ass
in a major way.

01:17:56.005 --> 01:17:57.047
What you did was dumb.

01:17:57.131 --> 01:18:00.258
What I'm asking here
is no big deal, Sam.
This is my daughter!

01:18:00.593 --> 01:18:02.010
No, Tom, it's perjury
and it's bullshit

01:18:02.094 --> 01:18:03.553
and I'm not doing it!
Now, excuse me.

01:18:04.013 --> 01:18:05.764
All right?
All right.
I'll be in my office.

01:18:06.390 --> 01:18:08.099
Tom, who was that
top criminal lawyer?

01:18:08.184 --> 01:18:09.934
Lee Heller.
Kersek.

01:18:10.019 --> 01:18:11.186
We need to talk.
KERSEK: Trouble is

01:18:11.270 --> 01:18:13.563
if word gets out
how Cady bushwhacked
those poor bastards,

01:18:13.647 --> 01:18:15.190
it's gonna be
a bitch to line up
three new guys.

01:18:15.274 --> 01:18:17.776
I don't want three new guys.
No more guys, you hear me?

01:18:17.860 --> 01:18:19.652
Mr. Heller,
it's Sam Bowden

01:18:19.737 --> 01:18:21.446
from Broadbent
and Denmeyer.

01:18:22.406 --> 01:18:23.656
Tom speaks
very highly of you.

01:18:23.741 --> 01:18:24.991
In fact,
he says you're the best,

01:18:25.076 --> 01:18:26.284
and the best is
what I need right now.

01:18:26.369 --> 01:18:28.620
HELLER: (ON PHONE)
We froze our butts
together in Korea.

01:18:28.704 --> 01:18:30.038
How can I help you,
Sam?

01:18:30.122 --> 01:18:32.874
Well, it's a simple petition
for a restraining order,

01:18:32.958 --> 01:18:34.751
but there's been
some complications.

01:18:34.835 --> 01:18:36.211
Now,
I know this is
short notice,

01:18:36.295 --> 01:18:38.213
but look,
I need this injunction.

01:18:38.297 --> 01:18:40.882
You see,
there's an ex-convict
by the name of Max Cady,

01:18:40.966 --> 01:18:42.008
he's been
harassing my family.

01:18:42.093 --> 01:18:45.637
I'm sorry, Mr. Bowden.
I can't continue
this conversation.

01:18:45.721 --> 01:18:47.430
Well, is there
a more convenient time?

01:18:47.515 --> 01:18:50.100
No, no. The damn thing
is I have a conflict.

01:18:50.184 --> 01:18:51.976
Now, what would
that be?
Well, you see,

01:18:52.061 --> 01:18:54.896
Mr. Cady retained
my services
as of yesterday.

01:18:54.980 --> 01:18:56.022
He what?

01:18:56.107 --> 01:18:58.024
In fact,
I see on my phone sheet

01:18:58.109 --> 01:18:59.651
Mr. Cady called
this morning,

01:18:59.735 --> 01:19:00.819
so I'm sure
he'll fill me in...

01:19:00.903 --> 01:19:04.531
But wait a minute, Lee.
Now, look, this man
is a psychotic.

01:19:04.615 --> 01:19:08.159
It appears
I'll be seeing you at
that hearing after all.

01:19:09.954 --> 01:19:11.162
CADY ON TAPE:
Could you repeat that?

01:19:11.247 --> 01:19:13.415
SAM ON TAPE: I said
if you don't leave...

01:19:14.417 --> 01:19:16.251
If you don't
leave my family alone

01:19:16.335 --> 01:19:18.503
and if you don't
get out of here,

01:19:18.587 --> 01:19:21.673
you're gonna be hurting
like you never dreamed.

01:19:22.675 --> 01:19:23.633
A threat?

01:19:23.717 --> 01:19:26.136
Yeah, you bet your ass
that's a threat.

01:19:27.346 --> 01:19:31.433
HELLER:
You need only glance
at my client to know

01:19:32.268 --> 01:19:34.477
that Mr. Bowden
made good

01:19:34.562 --> 01:19:37.897
on his heinous
and cowardly threat.

01:19:38.441 --> 01:19:40.775
Just as God arose
to judgment

01:19:40.860 --> 01:19:42.652
to save all the meek
of the earth,

01:19:42.736 --> 01:19:45.655
I hope and pray
you will do
the same, sir.

01:19:45.739 --> 01:19:47.323
Your Honor,
(CLEARS THROAT)

01:19:48.075 --> 01:19:51.286
Mr. Cady wouldn't
have surreptitiously
taped our meeting

01:19:51.370 --> 01:19:53.496
unless he knew
that he'd...

01:19:55.166 --> 01:19:59.043
This court
does not condone

01:20:00.004 --> 01:20:04.048
feuds, vendettas
or vigilantism.

01:20:04.633 --> 01:20:09.429
Let me quote our
great Negro educator,
Mr. Booker T. Washington.

01:20:10.222 --> 01:20:14.476
"I will let no man
drag me down so low

01:20:15.644 --> 01:20:18.062
"as to make me
hate him."

01:20:18.147 --> 01:20:19.230
Yes.

01:20:20.065 --> 01:20:22.734
I will grant
the restraining order

01:20:22.818 --> 01:20:26.321
not to validate
the malice between you,

01:20:26.405 --> 01:20:31.493
but in the interest
of Christian harmony.

01:20:33.078 --> 01:20:36.164
You may not come
within 500 yards

01:20:36.248 --> 01:20:40.835
of Mr. Maximilian Cady

01:20:41.587 --> 01:20:46.341
until such time
as the court may
lift the injunction.

01:20:47.968 --> 01:20:51.930
King Solomon could
not have adjudicated
more wisely, Your Honor.

01:20:52.723 --> 01:20:57.393
I am so offended by
the philistine tactics
of Mr. Bowden,

01:20:57.478 --> 01:21:01.689
I petitioned the A. B.A.
For his disbarment

01:21:01.774 --> 01:21:04.192
on the grounds of
moral turpitude.

01:21:04.527 --> 01:21:07.529
Now, if you will
excuse us, my client...

01:21:07.613 --> 01:21:08.613
Come on, son...

01:21:08.739 --> 01:21:10.448
Is due back
at the hospital

01:21:13.077 --> 01:21:17.497
for the results of
his numerous X-rays.

01:21:20.084 --> 01:21:21.209
Kersek, I want a gun.

01:21:21.669 --> 01:21:22.877
I need a gun.
I want a gun.

01:21:22.962 --> 01:21:24.128
You want a gun?

01:21:24.213 --> 01:21:25.296
Yeah, I need a gun.

01:21:25.965 --> 01:21:27.048
Know anything
about guns?
No.

01:21:27.132 --> 01:21:28.216
No, I don't believe
in them.

01:21:28.300 --> 01:21:29.759
I never had them
around the house
or anything.

01:21:29.843 --> 01:21:30.885
All right,
I'll get you a gun.

01:21:30.970 --> 01:21:32.387
What kind of
gun you want?
Now, calm down.

01:21:32.471 --> 01:21:34.472
Well, just something simple,
something I can handle.

01:21:34.557 --> 01:21:37.559
Let me see
what fits you. A.45...

01:21:37.643 --> 01:21:38.935
Let me see your hands.
Okay.

01:21:40.813 --> 01:21:43.064
A.38 snub-nosed
special. Yeah.
All right. Good.

01:21:43.148 --> 01:21:45.400
That'll do. I can even
teach you how to use it.

01:21:45.484 --> 01:21:47.360
All right. Great.
The first lesson
is this.

01:21:47.861 --> 01:21:50.238
Don't think of it
as shooting a man
or trying to kill him.

01:21:50.364 --> 01:21:52.407
Right.
Think of it as
an extension of your fist.

01:21:52.491 --> 01:21:54.492
You're just reaching out
and knocking the man down.

01:21:55.160 --> 01:21:56.160
All right.

01:21:56.245 --> 01:21:58.371
Later on we can
go out to the woods
and shoot some trees, okay?

01:21:58.455 --> 01:22:01.124
That'd be great.
That'd be great. Good.

01:22:03.252 --> 01:22:05.003
What is it? What?

01:22:05.087 --> 01:22:06.921
Well, Sam...
Yeah?

01:22:07.006 --> 01:22:09.465
I give you a gun.
You pull it on Cady,

01:22:09.550 --> 01:22:10.592
and it's gonna
dawn on you

01:22:10.676 --> 01:22:11.676
that shooting a man
is different

01:22:11.760 --> 01:22:13.553
than blowing holes
in some tree.

01:22:13.637 --> 01:22:15.847
Next thing, you know,
you don't have my gun,
Cady does.

01:22:16.348 --> 01:22:17.390
No, no, no.
You're gonna teach me.

01:22:17.474 --> 01:22:18.891
I know how
to handle a gun.

01:22:18.976 --> 01:22:20.101
He won't take it
away from me.

01:22:20.185 --> 01:22:23.146
Best-case scenario,
you kill Cady dog-dead.

01:22:24.148 --> 01:22:27.525
Fifteen years to life.
Do you realize that,
Counselor?

01:22:33.324 --> 01:22:36.200
Oh, Jesus!
It's all fucked up,
Kersek!

01:22:37.077 --> 01:22:38.328
I mean,
the law considers me

01:22:38.412 --> 01:22:40.246
more of a loose cannon
than Max Cady!

01:22:40.331 --> 01:22:42.624
Some big-shit attorney
has whipped

01:22:42.708 --> 01:22:44.959
the A. B.A.'s
ethics committee
into a frenzy.

01:22:45.461 --> 01:22:48.296
There's an emergency session
in Raleigh over the assault.

01:22:48.672 --> 01:22:50.381
How did they link that
to you?

01:22:50.549 --> 01:22:54.677
I went to warn Cady.
I thought it was
the decent thing to do.

01:22:54.762 --> 01:22:57.722
Maybe I'd scare him.
And he was wired.

01:23:00.476 --> 01:23:02.310
Goddamn fools.

01:23:05.773 --> 01:23:07.649
This hearing,
it's real important?

01:23:07.733 --> 01:23:09.233
(LAUGHS)

01:23:09.902 --> 01:23:13.404
Only if I want to continue
to practice law. Yeah.

01:23:14.531 --> 01:23:15.573
Cady isn't
expected there, is he?

01:23:16.075 --> 01:23:19.369
Oh, no, no, no.
Mr. Cady,
he's beyond reproach.

01:23:19.495 --> 01:23:21.162
But you're required
to be there.
Yeah.

01:23:22.456 --> 01:23:23.498
When is this hearing?

01:23:23.582 --> 01:23:25.667
It's Thursday morning,
9:00.

01:23:25.751 --> 01:23:28.503
The torture begins
and lasts for two days.

01:23:29.713 --> 01:23:31.005
You have to fly up
the night before?

01:23:31.965 --> 01:23:33.132
Right.

01:23:34.051 --> 01:23:35.843
Cady's an opportunist.

01:23:35.928 --> 01:23:37.887
If he thinks
you're gonna be out
of town for two days,

01:23:37.971 --> 01:23:40.682
that's going to be
as tempting to him
as shit is to a fly.

01:23:41.433 --> 01:23:43.017
If Cady breaks
into your home,

01:23:43.102 --> 01:23:44.811
he can be killed.

01:23:44.895 --> 01:23:46.270
Justifiably.

01:23:48.315 --> 01:23:51.067
But he won't show
unless he's real sure
you're not gonna be there.

01:24:29.148 --> 01:24:30.481
(SWITCHING STATIONS)

01:24:32.151 --> 01:24:34.110
(CHOIR SINGING)

01:25:00.304 --> 01:25:01.304
Have a good trip.

01:25:01.388 --> 01:25:03.097
All right. Bye-bye.

01:25:03.182 --> 01:25:04.182
Call us tonight, okay?

01:25:04.266 --> 01:25:05.600
All right.

01:25:16.028 --> 01:25:17.612
I didn't miss
the 9:20 to Raleigh?

01:25:17.696 --> 01:25:19.989
I'm afraid you did, sir.
But there's a 10:20.

01:25:20.073 --> 01:25:21.157
Oh, it's not that.

01:25:21.241 --> 01:25:24.202
I just have some very,
very important papers
for Samuel Bowden.

01:25:24.703 --> 01:25:25.953
Was he on the 9:20?

01:25:26.872 --> 01:25:28.581
We can't give out
that information, sir.

01:25:29.374 --> 01:25:30.875
Well, it's just...

01:25:31.668 --> 01:25:33.544
I guess I could send it
to him overnight,

01:25:33.629 --> 01:25:37.381
but he might be back,
for all I know,
tomorrow morning, and I...

01:25:38.717 --> 01:25:40.051
See, I...

01:25:40.427 --> 01:25:43.721
My wife and I have
been in an accident,
and he's our lawyer.

01:25:43.806 --> 01:25:47.975
And if I don't get
in touch with him,
we could lose this case.

01:25:48.060 --> 01:25:50.978
We've already lost
our little daughter, Dani.

01:25:52.231 --> 01:25:53.356
Is...

01:25:55.067 --> 01:25:56.234
Is there any way
I can find out

01:25:56.318 --> 01:25:59.028
if he was on that flight
and when he's coming back?

01:25:59.112 --> 01:26:01.239
It'd really,
really help us.

01:26:03.826 --> 01:26:04.909
(KEYS CLATTERING)

01:26:11.375 --> 01:26:13.334
He'll be back the day
after tomorrow, sir.

01:26:14.086 --> 01:26:15.711
Bless your heart.

01:26:30.936 --> 01:26:32.520
(SOFTLY)
Go on. Go on in.

01:26:35.274 --> 01:26:36.774
Get down, Sam.

01:26:42.155 --> 01:26:44.407
(BANGING ON DOOR)
Leigh. Leigh,
give me a cigarette.

01:26:45.784 --> 01:26:46.951
You better
slow down, Sam.

01:26:47.035 --> 01:26:48.995
You're outpacing me
two-to-one since
you started smoking.

01:26:49.079 --> 01:26:51.706
Just keep track of
how many I owe you.

01:26:53.625 --> 01:26:54.750
So, how'd it go
at the airport?

01:26:54.835 --> 01:26:56.043
Well, we did our thing,

01:26:56.128 --> 01:26:57.461
but we don't know
if he saw us,

01:26:57.546 --> 01:26:59.589
we don't even know
if he was there.

01:27:00.090 --> 01:27:02.133
Set the trap
and we'll see.

01:27:02.676 --> 01:27:03.843
What if we don't
want to see?

01:27:04.219 --> 01:27:05.595
Dani!
DANIELLE: What?

01:27:05.888 --> 01:27:07.763
Maybe he
poisoned the dog.

01:27:08.098 --> 01:27:10.057
Dani...
Sam, watch out
for the windows.

01:27:10.142 --> 01:27:13.144
Yeah, you're not
allowed to stand up,
Dad, remember?

01:27:19.735 --> 01:27:20.902
Didn't Cady
go after her?

01:27:20.986 --> 01:27:22.153
LEIGH:
You don't know Dani.

01:27:22.237 --> 01:27:24.238
If she finds
a palmetto bug
in her bedroom,

01:27:24.323 --> 01:27:26.073
she takes it outside.

01:27:26.158 --> 01:27:28.534
You know, she could
never kill anything.

01:27:28.619 --> 01:27:30.077
Even a six-foot
palmetto bug?

01:27:30.162 --> 01:27:31.495
(LAUGHS)

01:27:32.998 --> 01:27:34.498
Oh, God.

01:27:43.300 --> 01:27:44.342
What is that?

01:27:45.594 --> 01:27:49.055
It's a monofilament line.
I got it from
Sam's fishing gear.

01:27:49.139 --> 01:27:51.807
See, what I do is
I stretch it across
the windows and the doors

01:27:51.892 --> 01:27:53.893
and tie it to
Dani's teddy bear here.

01:27:53.977 --> 01:27:55.561
If the bear moves
a quarter of an inch,

01:27:55.646 --> 01:27:57.188
I'll know
if the holy ghost
is sneaking in.

01:28:29.388 --> 01:28:31.180
What are you reading?

01:28:35.268 --> 01:28:36.435
Why? Did Kersek quit?

01:28:36.520 --> 01:28:37.603
No.

01:28:38.647 --> 01:28:40.481
It's just
that Cady said...

01:28:40.565 --> 01:28:42.400
You want some answers.

01:28:43.902 --> 01:28:45.111
Me, too.

01:28:47.406 --> 01:28:52.284
I'd like to know just
how strong we are
or how weak.

01:28:54.913 --> 01:28:56.706
But I guess
the only way we're going
to find that out

01:28:56.790 --> 01:28:59.959
is just by
going through this.

01:29:03.797 --> 01:29:07.591
It's just that Cady said
to read the book between
Esther and Psalms.

01:29:08.510 --> 01:29:10.136
Which is which one?

01:29:10.637 --> 01:29:12.263
The Book of Job.

01:29:15.434 --> 01:29:18.269
Job was a good man.
He believed in God

01:29:19.396 --> 01:29:21.397
and God tested
his faith.

01:29:21.815 --> 01:29:24.108
He took away
everything he had,

01:29:25.736 --> 01:29:27.486
even his children.

01:29:31.283 --> 01:29:32.575
(GASPS)

01:29:43.795 --> 01:29:46.714
DANIELLE:
It's hideous, this plan.
I mean, barbaric.

01:29:46.798 --> 01:29:50.301
They're crazy.
My dad's turned
into some kind of...

01:29:50.385 --> 01:29:51.552
I don't know what.

01:29:51.636 --> 01:29:52.928
Barbaric.

01:29:53.013 --> 01:29:54.889
(SPEAKING SPANISH)

01:29:56.308 --> 01:30:00.561
Listen to your father.
Do what they say.
What else you can do?

01:30:00.645 --> 01:30:03.606
Leave. We could go
to the houseboat,
you know,

01:30:03.690 --> 01:30:05.733
and get lost
in any inlet.

01:30:10.489 --> 01:30:11.989
Dani, come on.

01:30:12.491 --> 01:30:14.200
Don't stay outside.

01:30:20.916 --> 01:30:25.336
You wanna know what
really disturbs me?
It's killing this guy.

01:30:26.630 --> 01:30:28.798
I mean,
taking a man's life.

01:30:30.717 --> 01:30:33.344
I don't know if
I can live with that.

01:30:33.595 --> 01:30:35.554
You may have to.

01:30:35.680 --> 01:30:37.723
Sam, just remember
the plan.
I know the plan.

01:30:38.683 --> 01:30:41.185
Damn, it's premeditated.
It's...

01:30:41.520 --> 01:30:44.855
It makes me an accomplice,
an accessory, an abettor.

01:30:45.440 --> 01:30:47.233
It's also excessive force.

01:30:47.609 --> 01:30:50.111
Sam,
the only thing excessive
we could do to Cady

01:30:50.195 --> 01:30:53.114
would be to gut him
and eat his liver.

01:30:53.198 --> 01:30:54.323
That might
be excessive.

01:30:54.407 --> 01:30:56.659
Jesus Christ,
Kersek, I'm serious.

01:30:56.743 --> 01:30:58.953
No, you're scared.

01:30:59.496 --> 01:31:02.998
But that's okay.
I want you to
savor that fear.

01:31:03.708 --> 01:31:05.918
You know,
the South evolved in fear.

01:31:06.002 --> 01:31:10.214
Fear of the Indian,
fear of the slave,
fear of the damn Union.

01:31:11.466 --> 01:31:14.552
The South has
a fine tradition
of savoring fear.

01:31:23.645 --> 01:31:25.146
(INAUDIBLE)

01:31:32.195 --> 01:31:33.863
SAM: What's the matter?

01:31:34.406 --> 01:31:36.532
Don't look over!
Don't look.

01:31:36.908 --> 01:31:38.868
(WHISPERING)
She's making me nervous.

01:31:40.245 --> 01:31:41.829
What would
she normally do

01:31:41.913 --> 01:31:43.664
if Sam wasn't around
to run her home?

01:31:43.999 --> 01:31:45.416
She'd stay...
SAM: She'd stay over.

01:31:46.251 --> 01:31:48.335
Well, then,
she stays over.

01:32:36.092 --> 01:32:37.509
(TICKING)

01:33:49.833 --> 01:33:51.458
(RATTLING)

01:34:01.803 --> 01:34:03.053
(SNIFFLING)

01:34:20.989 --> 01:34:22.031
Leigh?

01:34:24.576 --> 01:34:26.076
What?
Leigh.

01:34:26.578 --> 01:34:28.537
I know how
the dog died.

01:34:29.664 --> 01:34:31.373
Sam, are you dreaming?
No. No.

01:34:31.458 --> 01:34:32.875
I just had
the weirdest feeling

01:34:32.959 --> 01:34:35.210
he was already
in the house.

01:34:39.841 --> 01:34:41.133
(LIGHT THUD)

01:34:50.226 --> 01:34:52.269
Can't sleep,
huh, Miss Graciela?

01:34:52.354 --> 01:34:53.604
Yeah. It's hot.

01:34:53.688 --> 01:34:55.230
(SIGHS)

01:34:55.315 --> 01:34:57.316
You know,
I think it's the humidity

01:34:57.400 --> 01:34:59.318
that makes us all
so thirsty.

01:34:59.903 --> 01:35:02.237
(BURPS) Excuse me.

01:35:03.490 --> 01:35:05.157
My pop was a cop.

01:35:06.117 --> 01:35:07.618
Twenty years.

01:35:07.994 --> 01:35:10.329
This was his favorite drink
when he was on a stakeout.

01:35:12.916 --> 01:35:14.416
(CHOKING)

01:35:22.884 --> 01:35:24.134
(GUN FIRES)
(GASPS)

01:35:29.808 --> 01:35:32.351
I learned that
in prison. You like?

01:35:32.811 --> 01:35:34.561
White trash
piece of shit.

01:35:34.646 --> 01:35:35.979
(CHUCKLING)

01:35:43.947 --> 01:35:45.531
Stay here, Leigh.

01:35:51.704 --> 01:35:58.794
Kersek?

01:36:07.804 --> 01:36:10.722
Dani, Dani,
go back to your room.
Go back to your room.

01:36:10.807 --> 01:36:12.349
Lock the door.

01:36:15.186 --> 01:36:16.395
Kersek?

01:36:17.147 --> 01:36:18.564
(DOOR CLOSES)

01:36:19.190 --> 01:36:20.732
(WHISPERS) Don't go
down there, Sam.

01:36:20.817 --> 01:36:22.276
No, it's all right.

01:36:29.868 --> 01:36:31.034
Kersek?

01:36:38.877 --> 01:36:39.918
Sam?

01:36:42.881 --> 01:36:44.173
(GASPS)

01:36:48.219 --> 01:36:49.553
(SCREAMING)

01:36:49.929 --> 01:36:51.430
SAM: Dani, don't look.

01:36:51.723 --> 01:36:53.599
(SOBBING)
Oh, my God, Graciela!

01:36:53.683 --> 01:36:55.893
Dani, don't look.
Don't look, Dani.

01:36:57.437 --> 01:36:58.604
Oh, my God.

01:36:59.606 --> 01:37:01.190
DANIELLE: Oh, my God!

01:37:02.525 --> 01:37:09.615
Oh, my God!

01:37:09.699 --> 01:37:11.325
(DANIELLE CONTINUES SOBBING)

01:37:24.756 --> 01:37:25.839
It's the piano wire.

01:37:29.010 --> 01:37:30.093
LEIGH: Sam!

01:37:30.178 --> 01:37:31.720
(EXCLAIMS)

01:37:32.764 --> 01:37:34.056
I'm going to get
this son of a bitch!

01:37:34.140 --> 01:37:35.432
Sam!

01:37:35.683 --> 01:37:38.727
No! No! No!

01:37:39.938 --> 01:37:41.230
No!

01:37:41.356 --> 01:37:42.648
I'm gonna slit
that son of a bitch!

01:37:43.733 --> 01:37:45.901
Tell him to stop!

01:37:47.445 --> 01:37:51.323
God, he might be out here!
He might be out here!

01:38:30.822 --> 01:38:32.489
SAM: Now, listen,
I've got Kersek's
gun with me

01:38:32.574 --> 01:38:36.368
and you're gonna
find the piano wire that
Cady used in the house.

01:38:36.452 --> 01:38:38.579
Yeah, I know
how this looks.
I know it.

01:38:38.663 --> 01:38:41.290
You're not supposed
to flee a murder scene.

01:38:41.374 --> 01:38:43.959
Listen, Lieutenant, now,
you may know this
and you may not,

01:38:44.043 --> 01:38:46.837
but in the law,
there's a thing
called force majeure.

01:38:46.921 --> 01:38:49.423
It means
an unforeseeable act of God

01:38:49.507 --> 01:38:52.217
and it cancels
all promises
and obligations.

01:38:52.302 --> 01:38:54.678
So, legally speaking,
all bets are off.

01:38:55.054 --> 01:38:58.181
You find Max Cady
and we'll come back.

01:39:00.852 --> 01:39:01.893
What did he say?

01:39:01.978 --> 01:39:03.061
He said we're fugitives.

01:39:03.146 --> 01:39:04.104
DANIELLE:
What's that mean?

01:39:04.188 --> 01:39:05.981
SAM: That means we're
doing something right.

01:39:06.065 --> 01:39:07.482
(DOORS CLOSE)
(ENGINE STARTS)

01:39:33.968 --> 01:39:37.220
Where's that
old mongrel dog
of yours, Mrs. Bowden?

01:41:20.158 --> 01:41:21.742
(THUNDER RUMBLING)

01:41:58.029 --> 01:42:00.322
Tomorrow,
I'll catch some fish.

01:42:00.615 --> 01:42:02.324
Oh, you know,
you don't have to.

01:42:02.408 --> 01:42:04.284
I've got
enough food here
to last us a week.

01:42:13.377 --> 01:42:15.003
But it'd be nice.

01:42:16.172 --> 01:42:17.214
Good.

01:42:18.216 --> 01:42:19.966
(RAIN PATTERING)

01:42:20.843 --> 01:42:22.552
(CLATTERING)

01:42:26.516 --> 01:42:28.850
It's only rain.
A sheet of rain.

01:42:30.353 --> 01:42:31.770
(LEIGH EXCLAIMS)

01:42:33.064 --> 01:42:34.147
What was that?

01:42:34.232 --> 01:42:35.315
It's just a squall.

01:42:37.151 --> 01:42:38.151
I'll go check
the anchor.

01:42:38.236 --> 01:42:39.486
Wait, Dad.
Don't go out.

01:42:39.570 --> 01:42:42.447
No, Dani. Now, look,
everything is okay.
All right?

01:42:42.532 --> 01:42:44.074
Yeah. We're on
the river now, baby.

01:42:44.158 --> 01:42:45.659
It's just a squall
kicking up.

01:43:11.352 --> 01:43:13.645
Graciela has a brother.

01:43:13.729 --> 01:43:15.438
I mean, she had...

01:43:16.023 --> 01:43:17.399
